Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.74,0:45:21.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,毀了\N{\rENG}reconstructed.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.84,0:45:24.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,更糟的是...\N{\rENG}And what's worse...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.61,0:45:28.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,我沒法醒過來\N{\rENG}is that I can't wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.34,0:45:56.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,你家裡怎樣了...派對之後\N{\rENG}And how was your house after the party?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.55,0:45:59.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,派對?\N{\rENG}Party?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.52,0:46:02.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼派對?\N{\rENG}What party?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.02,0:46:04.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,就是那個派對啊\N{\rENG}The party.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.76,0:46:08.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,記得嗎?\N{\rENG}Remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.16,0:46:12.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,紅禮服, 系帶鞋\N{\rENG}Red dress, strappy shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.43,0:46:18.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,我把東西灑在你的襯衫上\N{\rENG}I spilled something on your shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.33,0:46:20.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,甜蜜和心酸\N{\rENG}Sweet and sour.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.70,0:46:25.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,一直拿著馬提尼的傷心女孩\N{\rENG}And the saddest girl to ever hold a martini.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.36,0:46:50.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的夢是一個殘酷的玩笑\N{\rENG}My dreams are a cruel joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.57,0:46:55.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,它們嘲諷我\N{\rENG}They taunt me.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.38,0:47:05.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,即使在夢裡, 我也是個傻瓜...\N{\rENG}Even in my dreams, I'm an idiot...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.82,0:47:08.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,知道自己就快要醒來面對現實\N{\rENG}who knows he's about to wake up to reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.72,0:47:14.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果我可以不睡的話...\N{\rENG}If I could only avoid sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.26,0:47:18.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,但我做不到\N{\rENG}But I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.43,0:47:20.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,我試著告訴自己做其他的夢\N{\rENG}I try to tell myself what to dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.17,0:47:24.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,我嘗試夢到自己在飛\N{\rENG}I try to dream that I'm flying.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.97,0:47:26.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,做些自由的事\N{\rENG}Something free.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.74,0:47:30.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,但沒有用\N{\rENG}It never works.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.08,0:47:41.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,那就是你唯一夢到的事?\N{\rENG}Is that the only thing you dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.49,0:47:45.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不...不記得了\N{\rENG}I don't- I don't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.13,0:47:53.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,你夢到那場車禍了嗎?\N{\rENG}Do you dream about the car accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.83,0:47:57.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,這就是你在昏迷中的記憶...\N{\rENG}Here's what you remember from a coma.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.40,0:47:59.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,...一片空白\N{\rENG}Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.74,0:48:05.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,接下來發生了什麼?\N{\rENG}What happened next?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.48,0:48:08.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,到底發生了什麼?\N{\rENG}What really happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.38,0:48:12.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼, 你沒看檔案嗎?\N{\rENG}What, didn't you read the file?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.38,0:48:14.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,我昏迷了三個半星期\N{\rENG}I was out for three-and-a-half weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.45,0:48:18.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的臉和手臂都破碎了, 下頜有四處骨折\N{\rENG}My face and my arm shattered and my jaw was broken in four places.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.62,0:48:23.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為昏迷無法實施外科手術\N{\rENG}No surgery could be performed because of the coma.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.36,0:48:27.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,你無法體會那種黑暗...\N{\rENG}You can't feel the darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.46,0:48:28.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有麻木\N{\rENG}or numbness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.03,0:48:32.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,你甚至毫無知覺\N{\rENG}You can't even feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.60,0:48:34.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,然後...\N{\rENG}And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.40,0:48:36.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,我又回到我的生活\N{\rENG}I came back to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.21,0:48:41.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,就像小狗班尼\N{\rENG}Just like that dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.31,0:48:43.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,班尼, 你知道, 那只小狗\N{\rENG}Benny. You know, Benny the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.78,0:48:46.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,班尼, 小狗班尼\N{\rENG}Benny. Benny the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.92,0:48:50.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,只是我的生活不再正常\N{\rENG}Only my life was no longer normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.19,0:48:54.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,神經損傷讓我頭痛欲裂\N{\rENG}There are blinding migraines now- nerve damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.79,0:48:56.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,為什麼?\N{\rENG}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.26,0:49:00.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,這就和大企業操縱...\N{\rENG}This is how big business operates-
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.20,0:49:02.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,隨機的意外一樣\N{\rENG}random accidents...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.33,0:49:04.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,一個生活中的事故\N{\rENG}a lifestyle mishap.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.93,0:49:06.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,這都不是巧合\N{\rENG}They are not coincidences.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.74,0:49:11.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不覺得再縝密的合同都會有破綻嗎?\N{\rENG}How do you think airtight contracts are broken?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.61,0:49:14.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,這都是因為權利的爭奪\N{\rENG}These are power upheavals.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.01,0:49:16.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是從鄉下來的\N{\rENG}I'm from Ohio.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.75,0:49:19.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們沒見過權利爭奪\N{\rENG}We don't have power upheavals.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.78,0:49:22.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,每天的新聞都有, 就在字裡行間\N{\rENG}They are in the news every day right between the lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.25,0:49:27.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,有人故意這樣對我\N{\rENG}Someone did this to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.69,0:49:31.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,我爸在他的書裡就寫過這些\N{\rENG}My father wrote about this in his book.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.13,0:49:33.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,第一章, 第一頁...\N{\rENG}Chapter one, page one...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.56,0:49:35.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,第一段\N{\rENG}paragraph one-
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.23,0:49:37.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,"一百個問題中有九十九個答案是什麼?\N{\rENG}"What is the answer to 99 out of 100 questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.44,0:49:42.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,錢."\N{\rENG}Money."
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.44,0:49:44.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,大衛, 聽著, 我不想讓你擔心\N{\rENG}David, look, I don't wanna worry you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.94,0:49:47.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,我正在應付, 但現在有個情況\N{\rENG}I'm holding them off, but we got a situation here.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.84,0:49:51.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,根據董事會的規章, 要保有你51%的股權...\N{\rENG}The bylaws of the board protect your 51 % vote...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.38,0:49:53.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,你必須心智正常\N{\rENG}only if you're mentally acute.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.35,0:49:56.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,我很遺憾那可憐的女孩死了...\N{\rENG}I'm sorry that poor girl died...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.45,0:49:59.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,但你還掌握著董事會, 真是不幸中的萬幸\N{\rENG}but you've handed the board a real gift with your mishap.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.49,0:50:02.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們想宣佈你讓權\N{\rENG}They'd like to declare you incapacitated.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.89,0:50:05.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,但你又回來了\N{\rENG}But you're back.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.93,0:50:09.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽到你的聲音真好, 就讓我們和那幫混蛋開戰吧...\N{\rENG}You sound good to me, so let's fight the fuckers...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.83,0:50:11.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,好好養傷\N{\rENG}and have a full recovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.83,0:50:14.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許你應該讓大家見見你?\N{\rENG}And maybe you should let people see you, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.20,0:50:17.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,上次我們一起去, 你還在昏迷...\N{\rENG}The last time we were together you were in a coma...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.21,0:50:19.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,你對我真他媽的沒禮貌\N{\rENG}and you were very fucking rude to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.81,0:50:22.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,你都沒說一句話\N{\rENG}You didn't say a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.55,0:50:26.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的, 關於我去世的謠言被有些誇大了\N{\rENG}Yes, well, the rumors of my death have been mildly exaggerated.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.02,0:50:32.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,我該相信誰?\N{\rENG}Who could I trust?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.06,0:50:35.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,螞蟻們都在蟻丘上議論紛紛呢\N{\rENG}The ants were taking over the anthill.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.86,0:50:39.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,我該相信誰?\N{\rENG}Who could I trust?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.66,0:51:44.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,頭骨打了30顆鋼釘...\N{\rENG}The cranial structure was based on 30 pins...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.43,0:51:47.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,並用下頜骨碎片固定\N{\rENG}and fastened by micro-panels and bits of bone from the mandible.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.00,0:51:50.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,看起來軟骨成型技術保持了你的臉部結構\N{\rENG}It appears the cartilage graphs have maintained your cheek structure.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.03,0:51:53.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,不幸的是, 由於你一直昏迷...\N{\rENG}Unfortunately, because you were in a coma-
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.10,0:51:56.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,醫生, 他們滿口術語, 那你只好做些功課...\N{\rENG}Doctors. Their power is in jargon, so you study up.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.87,0:52:00.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,這過程造成的雙側眶周血腫...\N{\rENG}Is that the procedure for all bilateral periorbital hematomas...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.28,0:52:02.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,是由於昏迷患者的勒福氏骨折嗎\N{\rENG}in a LeFort Three fracture of a comatose patient?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.31,0:52:04.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 勒福氏骨折?\N{\rENG}- ...你做到最好\N{\rENG}- In a LeFort Three? - You do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.31,0:52:05.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然\N{\rENG}Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.38,0:52:08.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,顱內腦損傷的機率太大了\N{\rENG}The potential for intracranial brain damage was too great.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.75,0:52:10.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,除了面部移植, 波梅蘭茲醫生...\N{\rENG}Beyond the cheek grafts, Dr. Pomeranz...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.85,0:52:13.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,是否用那些鋼釘固定...\N{\rENG}are the pins fastened with any kind of aluminum which could ionize...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.52,0:52:15.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,會在我腦袋裡造成壓力?\N{\rENG}and cause that pressure in my head?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.76,0:52:18.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我已準備接受手術\N{\rENG}- 我們正在研究\N{\rENG}- I'm ready for another operation. - We are working on processes.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.83,0:52:21.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,但你並不適合做手術, 我們還在實驗\N{\rENG}But you're specifically not at the stage where we can experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.60,0:52:26.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,實驗, 就用我吧\N{\rENG}Experiment. Use me.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.54,0:52:29.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,頭痛將會消失\N{\rENG}The headaches will go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.11,0:52:31.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,這不只是頭痛\N{\rENG}These are more than headaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.71,0:52:35.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,這就像用鋼板切斷了我所有的思想\N{\rENG}These are like steel plates slicing through my every thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.91,0:52:38.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們不是牛仔, 不會這樣隨意就做\N{\rENG}We're not cowboys. We can't just wing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.32,0:52:41.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,大部分時間我都無法認真思考\N{\rENG}Because I can't think straight most of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.72,0:52:44.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我們可以增加你的藥量\N{\rENG}- 噢, 是啊, 藥物\N{\rENG}- We can increase your medication. - Oh, yes, medication.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.52,0:52:49.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們會繼續研究方案\N{\rENG}And there are things that we'll continue to investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.53,0:52:52.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,不管怎樣, 有很多人都沒有這種效果...\N{\rENG}However, there are so many others who've not had the aesthetic benefit...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.30,0:52:54.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,像你整形出來這樣\N{\rENG}of plastic surgery as you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.47,0:52:59.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,這無關虛榮, 波梅蘭茲醫生\N{\rENG}This isn't about vanity, Dr. Pomeranz.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.34,0:53:01.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,這無關虛榮\N{\rENG}This isn't about vanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.34,0:53:03.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是關於正常的功能\N{\rENG}This is about functioning in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.44,0:53:05.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,完整的功能是我正常運作必須的\N{\rENG}It's my job to be out there functioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.58,0:53:09.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,我有錢, 我會出任意價格\N{\rENG}I've got the money. I'll pay any amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.51,0:53:12.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,發明些什麼吧\N{\rENG}Just invent something.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.52,0:53:14.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,發揮想像力\N{\rENG}Just play jazz.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.32,0:53:16.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們自稱是紐約最好的整形醫生\N{\rENG}You say you're the best face man in New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.52,0:53:18.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,他媽的證明給我看\N{\rENG}Fucking prove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.16,0:53:24.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我們可以給你的手臂做手術\N{\rENG}- 去他媽的手臂!\N{\rENG}- We could do something about your arm. - Fuck my arm!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.70,0:53:31.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,這兒沒人自以為能體會到你的感受\N{\rENG}Nobody here takes your feelings for granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.84,0:53:35.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,根據初步的診斷我們的確為你準備了一樣東西\N{\rENG}We did prepare something for you based on the preliminary examination.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.87,0:53:37.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,說吧, 拿出來\N{\rENG}Tell me. Bring it on.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.87,0:53:40.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,這在排斥反應的初期是很有用的\N{\rENG}It's sometimes useful in the early stages of rejection.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.61,0:53:44.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,是一個面部假體, 花了兩周才做好\N{\rENG}It's a facial prosthetic.\N{\rENG}It was two weeks in the making.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.48,0:53:46.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 謝謝, 卡莉 - 不客氣, 醫生\N{\rENG}- Thank you, Carly. - You're welcome, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.33,0:53:59.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,一個面部假體\N{\rENG}A facial prosthetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.33,0:54:01.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,作為外觀的替代品它的確很有效...\N{\rENG}The aesthetic replacement does work...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.40,0:54:04.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,無論心理上還是生理上\N{\rENG}emotionally and actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.30,0:54:07.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,面具上的塑膠還可以阻擋不良的射線...\N{\rENG}The plastic in the aesthetic shield also blocks out abusive rays...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.14,0:54:09.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,有助於細胞的重生\N{\rENG}and assists in the regeneration of cells.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.57,0:54:13.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,所以這是個外觀重建的護罩?\N{\rENG}So it's an aesthetic regenerative shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.98,0:54:15.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,正確, 完全地\N{\rENG}That's correct. Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.68,0:54:18.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,護罩的人體工學原理還能使其自我調整...\N{\rENG}The ergonomics of the plate barrier allows it to interact reflexively...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.82,0:54:21.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,與你的臉部動作緊密結合\N{\rENG}with the movements of your own face.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.35,0:54:22.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道了\N{\rENG}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.89,0:54:26.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 這是個有用的東西 - 好\N{\rENG}- It's a helpful unit. - Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.72,0:54:29.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為就這一會兒功夫裡, 我還以為我們只是在談論...\N{\rENG}Because for a minute there, I thought we were talking...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.69,0:54:32.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,一個他媽的面具!\N{\rENG}about a fucking mask!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.63,0:54:35.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,這就只是個面具...\N{\rENG}It's only a mask...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.03,0:54:38.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你這樣認為的話\N{\rENG}if you treat it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.10,0:54:41.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,太棒了, 萬聖節真是派上用場了\N{\rENG}It's great. This completely takes care of Halloween.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.94,0:54:47.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是其他那364天怎麼辦呢?\N{\rENG}But what about the other 364 days of the year?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.66,0:55:04.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,一個全新的我逐漸成形\N{\rENG}A new form of me began to take shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.23,0:55:08.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,我計畫著我的復出...\N{\rENG}I planned my reemergence...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.00,0:55:10.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,就像諾曼地登陸\N{\rENG}like the Normandy invasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.10,0:55:13.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,索菲亞, 索菲亞\N{\rENG}Sofia. Sofia.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.24,0:55:18.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,索菲亞.塞拉諾\N{\rENG}Sofia Serrano.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.01,0:55:20.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,我只會說\N{\rENG}I'll just say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.08,0:55:23.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,我做足了功課\N{\rENG}I did my homework.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.38,0:55:25.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,我看了每一份備忘錄\N{\rENG}I read every memo.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.92,0:55:28.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,湯瑪斯.提普是對的\N{\rENG}Thomas Tipp was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.32,0:55:30.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,人們會再閱讀\N{\rENG}People will read again.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.96,0:55:35.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,我通過視頻參加每月和七個矮人的董事會議\N{\rENG}I attended the monthly board meeting with the Seven Dwarfs by video hookup.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.63,0:55:37.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為人們不再買書了\N{\rENG}Because people aren't buying books.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.03,0:55:41.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 讓我們投資吧 - 噢, 天哪, 這是戰爭\N{\rENG}- Let's invest. - Oh, baby, this was war.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.07,0:55:45.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,我以這種方式變得越來越強, 我以前都不知道\N{\rENG}I grew stronger in ways I'd never known before.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.50,0:55:47.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,然後到了十二月五日...\N{\rENG}And on December 5...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.60,0:55:50.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的飛機佈滿了天空...\N{\rENG}my planes filled the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.21,0:55:53.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,大衛.埃姆斯的複出...\N{\rENG}The return of David Aames, Jr...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.38,0:55:55.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,國民老二2世\N{\rENG}Citizen Dildo.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.29,0:56:37.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不會相信這個...\N{\rENG}You won't believe this...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.59,0:56:42.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,但這是我的笑容\N{\rENG}but this is me smiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.03,0:56:50.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,好久不見\N{\rENG}It's been a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.97,0:56:54.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想找你, 但你的人不讓我進去\N{\rENG}I tried to see you, but your people wouldn't let me.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.67,0:56:57.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,我都不想見我, 好吧?\N{\rENG}I didn't want to see me, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.47,0:56:59.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是後來...\N{\rENG}But then...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.74,0:57:02.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,今天我醒來, 發現...\N{\rENG}I woke up today and finally...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.38,0:57:05.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,頭髮真好看\N{\rENG}a good hair day.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.89,0:57:10.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,你想和我約會嗎?\N{\rENG}You wanna get together?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.62,0:57:14.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然\N{\rENG}Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.63,0:57:19.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 真的嗎?\N{\rENG}- 讓我們出去做點什麼\N{\rENG}- What? - Let's go out and do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.56,0:57:21.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,這週末\N{\rENG}This weekend.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.40,0:57:23.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要取消幾個常式\N{\rENG}I'll cancel an operation or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.77,0:57:26.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們會很開心...\N{\rENG}We'll have fun...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.24,0:57:29.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為我是個玩家\N{\rENG}because I am all about fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.01,0:57:36.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,好的, 觀眾們, 今晚第一個嘉賓是一個神奇的生存故事\N{\rENG}Okay, folks, our first guest tonight is an amazing survival story.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.85,0:57:38.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,歡迎小狗班尼\N{\rENG}Please welcome Benny the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.65,0:57:47.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,歡迎來上節目, 謝謝你來這裡\N{\rENG}So welcome to the show. Thank you very much for being here.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.42,0:57:49.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 真的, 我很榮幸 - 我有很多問題\N{\rENG}- You bet. My pleasure. - I have so many questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.59,0:57:52.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,首先, 和我們談談班尼發生了什麼事\N{\rENG}To start off, tell us all what has happened to Benny.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.06,0:57:55.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,它經歷過什麼?\N{\rENG}What's Benny been through?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.27,0:57:58.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,好的, 班尼掉進了我家附近的河水裡\N{\rENG}Well, Benny fell into the water near our home.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.30,0:58:01.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,然後它被凍在凱科米什河裡\N{\rENG}And he was frozen in the Skykomish River.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.47,0:58:02.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 在華盛頓 - 沒錯\N{\rENG}- In Washington. - That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.74,0:58:06.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,我去釣魚, 正想著它已經失蹤三個月了\N{\rENG}I went fishing, thinking he'd been gone now for three months.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.48,0:58:09.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,然後發現它在一個冰塊裡\N{\rENG}And I see him in a block of ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.98,0:58:12.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,它現在已經被解凍了, 對嗎?\N{\rENG}He is thawed out now. Is that correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.85,0:58:16.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,它不再活蹦亂跳了, 我很擔心\N{\rENG}He's not moving a lot. I'm worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.62,0:58:19.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,我應該去拿個鉗子嗎? 我很擔心這小狗\N{\rENG}Should I get out some tongs? I'm worried about the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.39,0:58:22.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,不, 它沒事, 它只是少一些活潑\N{\rENG}No, he's fine. He's just lost a little bit of his friskiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.76,0:58:23.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,我也這麼想\N{\rENG}I would think so, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.06,0:58:27.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,索菲亞, 我是大衛, 又來吵你了\N{\rENG}It's David. I'm back in your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.73,0:58:30.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,今早我剛見過你\N{\rENG}I saw you earlier today.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.33,0:58:35.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,我正看到我們的老朋友小狗班尼...\N{\rENG}I was just watching our old friend Benny the dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.14,0:58:36.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,在上節目...\N{\rENG}on Conan...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.91,0:58:39.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,然後我想到你\N{\rENG}and I thought of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.01,0:58:42.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,無所謂了\N{\rENG}Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.65,0:58:47.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,很高興今天見到你\N{\rENG}I loved seeing you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.85,0:58:50.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會很快再見你的\N{\rENG}So I will see you soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.62,0:58:53.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是個很棒的舞者\N{\rENG}You're a great dancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.53,0:58:57.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,再見\N{\rENG}Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.01,0:59:49.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你在喝什麼? - 沒什麼\N{\rENG}- What you drinkin'? - Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.68,0:59:52.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,我有意來一杯廉價的, 含糖的, 朗姆酒加可樂\N{\rENG}I'm in the mood for a cheap, sugary, overpriced rum and Coke.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.85,0:59:55.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你要嗎? - 還有其他的?\N{\rENG}- So you want one? - Is there any other kind?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.39,0:59:57.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,我去買\N{\rENG}I'll get us some.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.52,0:59:59.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,洗手間在哪?\N{\rENG}Where is the bathroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.52,1:00:03.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,就在那個地方的後面...\N{\rENG}It's behind- over there by the place...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.19,1:00:05.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,那個看起來像比約克的女孩那邊\N{\rENG}by the girl who looks like Bjork.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.70,1:00:07.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我就回來 - 也許我應該...\N{\rENG}- I'll be right back. - Maybe I should-
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.97,1:00:13.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿, 老兄, 你看起來不錯, 你的書怎麼樣?\N{\rENG}Hey, man, you look good. How's your book?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.24,1:00:16.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 脫下來 - 不, 這是個面罩\N{\rENG}- Take it off. - No, this is a facial shield.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.14,1:00:19.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是個美觀的假體, 這些他媽的醫生...\N{\rENG}It's an aesthetic prosthesis these fucking doctors-
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.74,1:00:22.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,拿掉那面罩, 老兄, 它把我嚇壞了\N{\rENG}Take off the mask, man. It's freaking me out.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.15,1:00:23.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,不行\N{\rENG}I can't.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.88,1:00:27.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是我的臉, 這就是我的臉\N{\rENG}It's my face. This is my face.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.85,1:00:30.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,相信我, 那有點不一樣\N{\rENG}Trust me. It's a little different.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.12,1:00:33.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你覺得尷尬, 就走吧, 沒人要找你作伴\N{\rENG}If you're embarrassed, just go. Nobody asked you to chaperone.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.69,1:00:36.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 索菲亞找我來的 - 什麼?\N{\rENG}- Sofia asked me. - What?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.69,1:00:39.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,她不想獨自和我在一起? 真是胡扯!\N{\rENG}She didn't want to be alone with me? That's bullshit!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.23,1:00:42.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,我覺得我都已經他媽的能接受這整件事了\N{\rENG}Because I think I'm being pretty fucking cool about this whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.33,1:00:44.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,去和心理醫生說\N{\rENG}Talk to a shrink.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.33,1:00:47.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,或者有時間可以打給我, 而不是躲在你的公寓裡\N{\rENG}Or you can call me sometime instead of hiding in your apartment.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.90,1:00:50.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,別對一個女孩子這樣, 你只見過她一次\N{\rENG}Don't take it out on a girl you only met once.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.11,1:00:53.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是她說的嗎?\N{\rENG}Did she say that-
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.84,1:00:55.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,一次?\N{\rENG}once?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.41,1:00:57.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,她說了我只見過她一次嗎?\N{\rENG}Did she say that I met her once?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.41,1:00:59.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,打住, 好嗎?\N{\rENG}Just cut it out, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.28,1:01:01.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,我懷念以前的你\N{\rENG}I miss the old you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.92,1:01:03.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們都懷念以前的你...\N{\rENG}We all miss the old you...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.92,1:01:06.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為現在這個是個爛人\N{\rENG}because the new guy is shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.79,1:01:11.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,說錯了, 我愛你\N{\rENG}That came out wrong. I love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.16,1:01:12.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,某段時期\N{\rENG}Period.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.03,1:01:16.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你手臂怎麼樣, 老兄?  - 去你的, 布萊恩\N{\rENG}- How's your arm, man? - Fuck you, Brian.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.30,1:01:18.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,要不這樣...\N{\rENG}How 'bout...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.40,1:01:19.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,不要同情\N{\rENG}no sympathy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.07,1:01:23.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,要不這就是我們的約定, 好...嗎?\N{\rENG}How 'bout that's the deal we make, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.65,1:01:36.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,給我來杯百威和一小杯龍舌蘭\N{\rENG}Give me a Budweiser and a shot of tequila.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.49,1:01:38.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,哪種龍舌蘭?\N{\rENG}What kind of tequila?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.42,1:01:44.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你說什麼?  - 我說, 哪種龍舌蘭?\N{\rENG}- What did you say to me? - I said, what kind of tequila?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.33,1:01:47.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,為什麼不看著我的臉說, 婊子?\N{\rENG}Why don't you ask me to my face, bitch?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.17,1:01:54.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,培恩的, 如果你有的話\N{\rENG}Patrón, if you have it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.63,1:02:25.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,再來杯龍舌蘭和百威\N{\rENG}Another shot, another Bud.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.64,1:02:27.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 這杯免費\N{\rENG}- 為什麼?\N{\rENG}- This is on the house. - Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.54,1:02:30.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,就這樣, 婊子\N{\rENG}It just is, bitch.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.79,1:03:22.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,培恩!\N{\rENG}Patrón!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.20,1:03:34.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,老兄, 整一下你他媽的臉\N{\rENG}Dude, fix your fucking face.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.86,1:04:29.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 又見面了 - 又見面了\N{\rENG}- Hello again. - Hello again.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.59,1:04:30.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,我有個想法\N{\rENG}Idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.76,1:04:32.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓我們重新開始吧\N{\rENG}Let's start over.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.00,1:04:37.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,能幫我個忙嗎? 不打擾的話\N{\rENG}How 'bout if you help me? Unless I'm horning in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.70,1:04:39.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,哦, 你擾到了, 不過食物不錯\N{\rENG}Oh, you are, but the food is good.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.87,1:04:43.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,看, 我有個小麻煩, 有人跟蹤我\N{\rENG}See, I've got this little problem. I've got a stalker.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.34,1:04:48.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽起來沒什麼大不了. 我需要個擋箭牌\N{\rENG}Doesn't sound life-threatening. I need a cover.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.28,1:04:51.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,我需要你假裝我們在愉快的交談...\N{\rENG}I need for you to pretend that we're having a scintillating conversation...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.61,1:04:55.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,而你非常享受\N{\rENG}and you are wildly entertained.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.15,1:04:57.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道這很為難. 我會配合的\N{\rENG}I know it's tough. I'll improvise.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.09,1:04:59.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不是那樣說的\N{\rENG}I don't talk like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.82,1:05:04.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,她就在屋子另一邊, 正盯著我背後看\N{\rENG}She's right across the room. She's burning a hole in my back now.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.30,1:05:11.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,紅禮服, 系帶鞋\N{\rENG}Red dress, strappy shoes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.10,1:05:15.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒錯\N{\rENG}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.44,1:05:20.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想她就是那個最傷心的女孩...\N{\rENG}I think she is the saddest girl...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.44,1:05:22.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,一直拿著一杯馬提尼\N{\rENG}to ever hold a martini.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.52,1:05:37.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你還好吧?  - 不\N{\rENG}- Are you okay? - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.66,1:05:40.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,為什麼? 怎麼了? 是我嗎?\N{\rENG}Why? What's wrong? Is it me?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.86,1:05:44.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 是我嗎? - 以後再說\N{\rENG}- Is it me? - I'll tell you later.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.33,1:05:47.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 以後再說 - 不對勁, 拜託, 和我說啊\N{\rENG}- I'll tell you later. - Something's wrong. Please. Tell me now.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.37,1:05:49.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在就說出來\N{\rENG}Talk about it all right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.34,1:05:51.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 快說, 全都說出來 - 我以後會和你說!\N{\rENG}- Talk about it. Get it all out. - I'll tell you later!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.04,1:05:54.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,說所有的事情\N{\rENG}Say everything now.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.18,1:05:57.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,你就把所有事都說出來, 現在!快!快!\N{\rENG}Just say everything now. Now! Now! Now!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.88,1:06:01.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會在下輩子告訴你, 當我們都變成貓的時候\N{\rENG}I'll tell you in another life, when we are both cats.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.22,1:06:09.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,我無法相信你說了這些\N{\rENG}I can't believe you just said that.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.80,1:06:15.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是我聽過的最棒的事\N{\rENG}That is the greatest thing that I've ever heard.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.46,1:06:17.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,你這麼說可真是有趣啊\N{\rENG}That's hilarious that you said that.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.07,1:06:22.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,看, 你竟然這麼說\N{\rENG}See, that- You said that.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.84,1:06:25.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,這就是我愛你的地方\N{\rENG}That is what I love about you.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.51,1:06:28.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,這真是太好玩了\N{\rENG}That's hilarious.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.08,1:06:32.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會在下輩子告訴你, 當我們都變成貓的時候\N{\rENG}I'll tell you in another life, when we are both cats.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.78,1:06:34.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,貓!\N{\rENG}Cats!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.08,1:06:36.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,貓!\N{\rENG}Cats!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.92,1:06:43.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,那麼, 我們就在這分開吧\N{\rENG}Well, this is where I leave you.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.03,1:06:45.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要送你到家門口\N{\rENG}I'll walk you to your door.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.03,1:06:48.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我就住在轉角那邊 - 我有腳踏車\N{\rENG}- I live just around the corner. - I've got my bike here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.66,1:06:50.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我更想走路 - 別費力了\N{\rENG}- I'd rather walk. - Don't be a drag.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.87,1:06:53.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,你看不出來她想自己走?\N{\rENG}Can't you see she wants to go on her own?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.54,1:06:55.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,閉嘴, 你醉了\N{\rENG}Shut up. You're drunk.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.54,1:06:59.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,我也許是白癡, 但我沒喝醉\N{\rENG}I may be an idiot, but I'm not drunk.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.98,1:07:02.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,說真的, 我不需要你送我到家\N{\rENG}Seriously, I don't need you to walk me home.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.98,1:07:05.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝你\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.11,1:07:08.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,好吧, 那麼, 我們再打給你\N{\rENG}Okay, then. So we'll call you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.82,1:07:12.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,好的, 到時我們去看場電影什麼的\N{\rENG}We'll go catch a movie or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.02,1:07:15.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,那麼我們很快會再見的\N{\rENG}So we'll meet up soon.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.20,1:07:21.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們很快會再見的\N{\rENG}We'll meet up soon.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.81,1:07:33.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們會再打給你, 到時和我約會!\N{\rENG}We'll call you again to go out with me!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.08,1:07:36.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們再打給你\N{\rENG}We'll call you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.65,1:07:39.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,這玩得可真開心啊\N{\rENG}It's been a real blast.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.32,1:07:41.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,我祝你晚安\N{\rENG}I bid you good evening.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.52,1:07:43.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,等等, 等等, 你去哪?\N{\rENG}Wait, wait. Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.62,1:07:46.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的腳踏車, 就在那後面, 改天再找你玩\N{\rENG}My bike- it's back over there. We'll hang soon.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.86,1:07:49.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,帶上你的面具如果你想的話, 我已經習慣了\N{\rENG}And bring your mask if you want. I'm getting used to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.73,1:07:52.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,等一下\N{\rENG}Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.06,1:07:54.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼?\N{\rENG}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.10,1:07:58.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不知道\N{\rENG}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.03,1:08:01.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,你喝得有點多了, 有事明天打給我吧\N{\rENG}You drank a little too much. Call me tomorrow if you want.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.57,1:08:04.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,我希望明天我就死了\N{\rENG}Tomorrow I'll wish I was dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.21,1:08:09.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,不, 你不希望, 你只需要睡個覺\N{\rENG}No, you won't. You just need to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.28,1:08:16.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼?\N{\rENG}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.42,1:08:25.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,車禍前你和茱莉.吉雅妮說了什麼?\N{\rENG}What did you say to Julie GiannI the night of the accident?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.86,1:08:27.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼?\N{\rENG}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.70,1:08:32.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,你和她說她是個..炮友\N{\rENG}You told her she was a fuck buddy.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.57,1:08:33.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有\N{\rENG}Never.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.34,1:08:38.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,她火得有點過頭了\N{\rENG}She was a little more than pissed about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.74,1:08:42.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,你一直就為這破事耿耿於懷?\N{\rENG}Have you been harboring this shit all along?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.24,1:08:44.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,我從沒和她說過\N{\rENG}I never talked to her.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.58,1:08:49.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.52,1:08:54.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有...\N{\rENG}Anyway...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.39,1:08:58.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果我不是那個說你長得不醜的人, 那我是誰?\N{\rENG}who am I if I can't be the one to tell you you're not ugly?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.86,1:09:00.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,拜託\N{\rENG}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.63,1:09:03.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,勉強笑一個吧\N{\rENG}Give me a courtesy laugh.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.60,1:09:06.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢, 布萊恩, 我搞砸了\N{\rENG}Oh, Brian, I'm so fucked up.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.60,1:09:08.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,我真的搞砸了\N{\rENG}I'm just so fucked up.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.87,1:09:13.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿, 布萊恩, 拜託\N{\rENG}Hey, Brian, come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.95,1:09:17.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們是最好的朋友!\N{\rENG}We're best friends!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.98,1:09:20.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們是哥們!\N{\rENG}We're bros!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.28,1:09:23.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,拜託, 老兄, 我們是哥們\N{\rENG}Come on, man, we're bros.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.29,1:11:05.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,睜開你的眼睛\N{\rENG}Open your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.26,1:11:14.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是個很爛的博同情的方式\N{\rENG}This is a cheap ploy for sympathy.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.63,1:11:18.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,我沒事, 我沒事\N{\rENG}I'm okay. I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.53,1:11:20.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,但起作用了, 起來吧\N{\rENG}And it worked. Get up.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.14,1:11:23.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,服你了\N{\rENG}I agree.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.41,1:11:28.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是個玩笑吧\N{\rENG}This is a joke.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.78,1:11:31.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,大衛, 我不想騙你\N{\rENG}David, I'm not gonna lie to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.48,1:11:33.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,我喜歡曾經的你\N{\rENG}I liked the way you looked.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.15,1:11:36.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,但...\N{\rENG}But...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.15,1:11:38.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,你得他媽的振作起來\N{\rENG}you have to pull it the fuck together.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.02,1:11:42.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,否則的話, 我就會把那個人忘了\N{\rENG}Because if not, I'll forget the other guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.22,1:11:45.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,你還知道那個人吧?  你\N{\rENG}You know that other guy? You.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.70,1:11:49.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,我還是那個人, 我還和以前一樣\N{\rENG}I'm still that guy. I'm still that guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.70,1:11:52.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽好, 我骨子裡可不是個慈祥的人\N{\rENG}I don't have a mother-savior bone in my body.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.90,1:11:56.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,和那無關, 你進來吧\N{\rENG}It's not about that. You are coming inside.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.47,1:11:59.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,但如果事實證明這是個大錯...\N{\rENG}But if this turns out to be a big mistake...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.31,1:12:03.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,我也能停止不去愛你...\N{\rENG}I do have the ability to fall out of love with you...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.08,1:12:05.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,就像這樣簡單\N{\rENG}like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.62,1:12:17.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們一起創造了我們的世界\N{\rENG}We created our own world together.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.63,1:12:19.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我還和以前一樣\N{\rENG}- 閉嘴\N{\rENG}- I am still that guy. - Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.36,1:12:21.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們與世俗抗爭\N{\rENG}Us versus them.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.40,1:12:23.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 布萊恩在哪?\N{\rENG}- 布萊恩?\N{\rENG}- Where's Brian? - Brian?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.47,1:12:26.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,他跑去找你了, 不是嗎?\N{\rENG}He went with you, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.54,1:12:28.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,我以為你們好上了\N{\rENG}I thought you guys hooked up.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.44,1:12:33.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,我真希望你從沒上那女孩的車\N{\rENG}I wish you hadn't gotten in the car with that girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.05,1:12:38.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,索菲亞, 我...\N{\rENG}Sofia, I-
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.38,1:12:43.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,你用眼神來道歉吧\N{\rENG}Your eyes apologize better.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.79,1:12:47.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,來吧\N{\rENG}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.36,1:12:51.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,天哪, 這將會令我的生活...\N{\rENG}Holy God, this is going to change my life...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.56,1:12:54.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,發生翻天覆地的變化\N{\rENG}in a zillion different ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.56,1:12:56.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,我一定是瘋了\N{\rENG}I must be nuts.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.67,1:12:58.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們是天生一對\N{\rENG}And we were quite a pair.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.67,1:13:01.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,她相信我, 我也覺得...\N{\rENG}Her believing in me, me believing that...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.90,1:13:04.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,我值得她這樣\N{\rENG}I actually deserved it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.47,1:13:22.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,索菲亞...\N{\rENG}Sofia...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.69,1:13:25.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,我看你沒在浪費時間\N{\rENG}I see you haven't been wasting your time.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.53,1:13:28.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,你還畫過其他的嗎?\N{\rENG}Do you ever draw anything else?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.62,1:13:32.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒\N{\rENG}No
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.70,1:13:34.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,昨晚睡了嗎?\N{\rENG}Did you sleep last night?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.21,1:13:38.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒, 沒睡\N{\rENG}No, I did not sleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.51,1:13:41.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,我今天得早走, 你得長話短說\N{\rENG}Got to leave early today, so you'll have to be brief.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.48,1:13:44.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,那, 你能告訴我些什麼...\N{\rENG}Now, what can you tell me...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.61,1:13:46.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,是有關於這名字"艾莉"的?\N{\rENG}about the name "Ellie"?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.45,1:13:51.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,艾莉\N{\rENG}Ellie.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.35,1:13:54.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,是你認識的女孩? 你愛過的女孩?\N{\rENG}Is that a girl you knew, a girl you were in love with?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.22,1:13:56.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,我只愛過一次\N{\rENG}I've only been in love once.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.53,1:13:59.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,很顯然, 昨晚你一直在喊她的名字\N{\rENG}Apparently, you kept repeating it last night.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.66,1:14:03.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,你有睡覺, 大衛, 你的導師說你喊出來了\N{\rENG}You did sleep, David. Your advisor said you cried out.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.77,1:14:06.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你做了個噩夢\N{\rENG}- 這一切都是噩夢\N{\rENG}- You had a nightmare. - Everything's a nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.34,1:14:10.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,你在喊艾莉, 大衛, 記得發生了什麼嗎?\N{\rENG}You cried out for Ellie, David. Do you remember what happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.79,1:14:17.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,我, 我不記得...\N{\rENG}I, I no...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.51,1:14:19.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,仔細想, 大衛\N{\rENG}Dig deep, David.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.31,1:14:21.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,仔細想\N{\rENG}Dig deep.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.25,1:14:24.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,你在喊艾莉, 你記得什麼嗎?\N{\rENG}You cried out for Ellie. What do you remember about Ellie?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.12,1:14:29.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,給我看你的臉, 大衛\N{\rENG}Show me your face, David.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.09,1:14:33.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,幫我開啟那道門\N{\rENG}Help me open the door.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.54,1:14:47.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的確是出了車禍, 你的確被毀容了\N{\rENG}It's true you had an accident. It's true you were disfigured.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.61,1:14:50.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,但你恢復了\N{\rENG}But not anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.15,1:14:52.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,記得嗎?\N{\rENG}Do you remember?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.12,1:14:56.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們的確修復了你的臉\N{\rENG}They did fix your face.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.55,1:15:01.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,把面具摘掉, 大衛\N{\rENG}Take off that mask, David.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.46,1:15:03.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,你會看到下面那張完美的臉\N{\rENG}You'll see your face is perfect under there.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.16,1:15:07.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,我從不相信醫生\N{\rENG}I never trusted the doctors.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.50,1:15:12.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,接下來的事更離奇\N{\rENG}What happened next was surreal.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.77,1:15:17.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,那個傲慢的混蛋, 波梅蘭茲醫生, 打電話給我\N{\rENG}That same arrogant bastard, Dr. Pomeranz, called me.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.11,1:15:19.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,突然間他成為我的好朋友\N{\rENG}Suddenly he was my new best friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.68,1:15:22.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,大衛, 嘿, 哥們\N{\rENG}David! Hey, my brother.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.31,1:15:24.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,對上次的談話我感到內疚\N{\rENG}I felt really bad about our last conversation.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.78,1:15:28.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,他說他發明了一個新的整形方式...\N{\rENG}He said he'd discovered a new form of reconstructive surgery...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.18,1:15:30.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,得到了來自柏林的醫生的幫助\N{\rENG}with the help of a doctor from Berlin.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.75,1:15:31.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,你好\N{\rENG}Hello.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.09,1:15:35.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,接下來, 他們用不知什麼藥物給我全身麻醉...\N{\rENG}Next thing I knew, they shot me full of drugs I'd never heard of...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.79,1:15:38.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,然後去手術室\N{\rENG}and away we went.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.46,1:15:42.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果上帝是我們中的一員\N{\rENG}What if God was one of us
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.13,1:15:48.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,也就跟我們差不多\N{\rENG}Just a slob like one of us
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.10,1:15:51.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,努力尋找回家的路\N{\rENG}Trying to make his way home
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.34,1:15:53.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,他嗓子不錯\N{\rENG}He's got a good voice.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.98,1:15:55.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,55\N{\rENG}Fifty-five.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.28,1:15:57.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,那個概率, 他們說, 有三分之一可能...\N{\rENG}The odds, they said, were one in three...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.65,1:16:00.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,會讓頭痛減輕50%...\N{\rENG}that the headaches could be reduced by 50 percent...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.12,1:16:02.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,並且重建面部組織\N{\rENG}and facial tissue could be regenerated.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.65,1:16:07.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,首次運用光纖重建眶骨膜的概念\N{\rENG}The first to incorporate the concept of endoscopic periorbital fiber optics.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.29,1:16:08.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,等下哪吃去?\N{\rENG}Where are we gonna eat later?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.02,1:16:11.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,我無法告訴你他們做了什麼\N{\rENG}I can't even tell you what they did.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.13,1:16:13.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,看起來就像科幻小說\N{\rENG}It seemed like science fiction to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.46,1:16:15.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道麥當娜有首歌"邊緣"\N{\rENG}Madonna had that song, "Borderline."
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.46,1:16:17.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 那首很好聽\N{\rENG}- ...剪一下\N{\rENG}- That was a hell of a song. - And another snip.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.67,1:16:20.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們完成後他就會變成個大帥哥\N{\rENG}This is gonna be one good-looking guy when I'm done.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.07,1:16:23.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,顯然, 我很懷疑\N{\rENG}Obviously, I was suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.67,1:16:26.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不會嗎?\N{\rENG}Wouldn't you be?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.08,1:16:29.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,懷疑誰, 懷疑什麼?\N{\rENG}Suspicious of whom, of what?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.81,1:16:30.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,醫生...\N{\rENG}Doc...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.98,1:16:34.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,一旦你以時速八十英里沖下一座橋...\N{\rENG}once you've been driven off a bridge at 80 miles an hour...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.75,1:16:38.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,不知為何你很難再快樂起來, 除非有十足把握\N{\rENG}somehow you don't invite happiness in without a full body search.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.09,1:16:45.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,不怕煩你\N{\rENG}At the risk of boring you...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.53,1:16:47.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,我有不同的看法\N{\rENG}I can present the alternate argument.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.33,1:16:51.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,我曾經認識一個人...\N{\rENG}I once knew a guy...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.60,1:16:53.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,他很孤單\N{\rENG}who was a real loner.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.64,1:16:56.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,直到他40歲某天...\N{\rENG}One day he woke up at 40...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.81,1:16:59.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,兩個女兒讓他覺得生命有了意義...\N{\rENG}with two daughters that lit up his life with purpose...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.78,1:17:02.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,然後他開始經常去看學校的表演...\N{\rENG}and he suddenly goes to endless school plays...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.88,1:17:05.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,9點半就回家聊天...\N{\rENG}and he gets home at 9:20\N{\rENG}for the evening discussion...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.61,1:17:09.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,他過著最快樂的時光\N{\rENG}and he has the time of his life.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.99,1:17:13.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,他最喜歡的甲殼蟲人物曾經是約翰, 現在是保羅\N{\rENG}His favorite Beatle was once John, and now it's Paul.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.56,1:17:18.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,我一直喜歡喬治\N{\rENG}I always liked George.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.30,1:17:23.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,這完全取決於個人, 不是嗎\N{\rENG}It all depends on the individual, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.67,1:17:25.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴我, 幸福對你來說是什麼?\N{\rENG}Tell me, what's happiness for you?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.87,1:17:28.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,幸福對你來說是什麼, 大衛?\N{\rENG}What's happiness to you, David?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.50,1:17:32.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 可以問其他問題嗎?\N{\rENG}- 你不給我看你的臉\N{\rENG}- How 'bout another question? - You won't show me your face.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.34,1:17:34.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,給嗎?\N{\rENG}Will you?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.24,1:17:37.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,那就回到原來的談話吧\N{\rENG}So back to the time line.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.08,1:17:40.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,快, 讓我們快點結束這些\N{\rENG}Hurry. Let's move through this.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.59,1:17:46.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼?\N{\rENG}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.32,1:17:50.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,你得把面具脫掉\N{\rENG}You've got to take the plates off.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.36,1:17:52.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不想看到下面是什麼\N{\rENG}I don't want to know what's under here.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.79,1:17:54.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒事的, 到時你就知道了\N{\rENG}It's gonna be fine. You'll see.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.86,1:17:56.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我明天再去\N{\rENG}- 你今天就去\N{\rENG}- I'll go tomorrow. - Today.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.40,1:17:58.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,我已經打給波梅蘭茲改到週三了\N{\rENG}I already called Pomeranz and switched it to Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.97,1:18:05.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼?\N{\rENG}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.48,1:18:10.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,我希望你被前臺護士罵死\N{\rENG}I hope that woman at the front desk gave you shit about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.55,1:18:16.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,改天沒事的,而且野馬汽車就要修好了\N{\rENG}Another day won't matter. Besides, the Mustang will be fixed.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.25,1:18:19.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,原計劃是要開野馬去, 但沒好...\N{\rENG}The plan was going in the Mustang. The Mustang's not ready.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.59,1:18:21.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,所以我們明天再去\N{\rENG}So we'll go tomorrow in the Mustang.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.49,1:18:23.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 好吧 - 等它修好了我們就去\N{\rENG}- Good. - We'll go when it's fixed.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.89,1:18:25.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道問題是什麼...\N{\rENG}I know that the problem...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.09,1:18:30.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不會是在拖延你不敢面對的事吧\N{\rENG}wouldn't be you delaying something you were dreading.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.10,1:18:34.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,不是\N{\rENG}Couldn't be that.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.37,1:18:36.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然不是\N{\rENG}Couldn't be that.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.44,1:18:40.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是說\N{\rENG}I mean-
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.18,1:18:52.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是說, 我同意\N{\rENG}I mean, I agree.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.36,1:18:56.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,我覺得這很重要...\N{\rENG}I think it's very important...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.69,1:18:58.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,開著...\N{\rENG}to have...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.70,1:19:02.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,心愛的車...\N{\rENG}the right car...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.97,1:19:11.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,帶你到...\N{\rENG}to take you...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.98,1:19:16.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,想去的地方...\N{\rENG}where you want to go...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.22,1:19:23.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,一天二十四小時...\N{\rENG}24 hours a day.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.98,1:19:50.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,有多糟?\N{\rENG}How bad is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.28,1:19:57.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,額, 你的耳朵處在正確的位置\N{\rENG}Well, your ears are in the right place.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.36,1:20:02.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,其他的嘛...\N{\rENG}And the rest of it...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.13,1:20:07.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,總的來說不錯\N{\rENG}is not too bad at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.40,1:20:14.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,太完美了\N{\rENG}It's perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.40,1:20:34.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,#鮑勃.狄倫的歌曲#\N{\rENG}#music#
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.75,1:21:08.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,你愛我嗎?\N{\rENG}Do you love me?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.12,1:21:10.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是說, 真的愛嗎?\N{\rENG}I mean, really love me?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.39,1:21:13.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為如果你不愛的話...\N{\rENG}Because if you don't...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.19,1:21:15.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,我就只好殺了你\N{\rENG}I'll just have to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.07,1:21:21.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的下輩子\N{\rENG}You see, my next life?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.10,1:21:22.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,在我的下輩子...\N{\rENG}In my next life...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.94,1:21:25.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會投胎變成這裡的這顆痣\N{\rENG}I'm gonna come back as this mole right here.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.88,1:21:29.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,說真的, 這顆痣\N{\rENG}Seriously, this mole.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.68,1:21:32.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,你只能穿比基尼和低胸的襯衣上班...\N{\rENG}You'll have to wear bikini tops to work and loose-fitting shirts...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.88,1:21:35.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,這樣我才能透氣\N{\rENG}so that I can breathe.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.48,1:21:38.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,我愛你\N{\rENG}I love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.29,1:21:39.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛你\N{\rENG}Love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.99,1:21:43.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,我愛你\N{\rENG}I love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.76,1:21:47.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,我可以住在這裡\N{\rENG}I can live right there.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.57,1:21:54.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是個夢嗎?\N{\rENG}Is this a dream?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.57,1:21:56.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,絕對是\N{\rENG}Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.00,1:22:08.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,[ 注:此場景來源於鮑勃.狄倫某張專輯的封面 ]\N{\rENG}# special scene #
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.12,1:22:11.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們聊大事, 小事...\N{\rENG}We talked about the big things, the little things...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.35,1:22:13.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,大事...\N{\rENG}and the big things.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.36,1:22:16.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,但事實上, 和索菲亞在一起...\N{\rENG}But in truth, with Sofia...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.89,1:22:19.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼都不聊都很快樂\N{\rENG}it was the in-between times.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.55,1:22:44.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,她說什麼?\N{\rENG}What did she say?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.05,1:22:46.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,我聽不懂\N{\rENG}I have no idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.23,1:22:52.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 過得如何, 布萊恩? - 很好\N{\rENG}- How's things, Brian? - Fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.23,1:22:56.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 布萊恩, 過得如何?\N{\rENG}- 別得意過頭了\N{\rENG}- Brian, How's things? - Don't flatter yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.73,1:22:58.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,我很好\N{\rENG}I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.40,1:23:01.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,而且, 索菲亞很好, 但並不意味著獨一無二\N{\rENG}Besides, Sofia is great but by no means one of a kind.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.77,1:23:03.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,她只是我一時的迷戀\N{\rENG}She was a proximity infatuation.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.21,1:23:09.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,別抄那句, 那是我的, 謝謝\N{\rENG}And don't use that. It's mine. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.41,1:23:12.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,你從哪弄的這像機?\N{\rENG}Where'd you get this camera?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.41,1:23:15.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的愛好, 你都不知道, 老兄\N{\rENG}I'm into things. You have no idea, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.19,1:23:19.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,你沒事就好\N{\rENG}Just as long as you're okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.45,1:23:21.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有, 我們是朋友, 不是嗎?\N{\rENG}And anyway, we're friends, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.72,1:23:23.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 一直都是\N{\rENG}- 沒錯\N{\rENG}- Always. - That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.57,1:23:37.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的臉怎麼了?\N{\rENG}What's up with your face?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.34,1:23:40.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 操! - 什麼?\N{\rENG}- Fuck! - What?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.98,1:23:42.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,有條縫還是什麼的裂開了!\N{\rENG}There's a seam opening or something!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.75,1:23:51.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 大衛.埃姆斯\N{\rENG}- 你這混蛋\N{\rENG}- David Aames. - You fucking asshole.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.72,1:23:54.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道\N{\rENG}I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.57,1:25:16.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,我剛才在打呼嗎?\N{\rENG}Was I snoring?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.17,1:25:22.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有,我覺得是我\N{\rENG}No, I think it was me.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.41,1:25:24.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,我只是口渴了\N{\rENG}I was thirsty, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.42,1:25:29.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,我夢見你了\N{\rENG}I'm dreaming about you.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.17,1:26:47.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,真想一直聽你"嗯"...\N{\rENG}I could listen to you say "mmm"...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.07,1:26:50.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,就這樣一輩子\N{\rENG}for the rest of my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.69,1:27:04.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,寶貝, 怎麼了?\N{\rENG}Baby, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.03,1:27:12.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,她在哪?\N{\rENG}Where is she?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.50,1:27:13.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,誰?\N{\rENG}Who?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.97,1:27:19.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,誰?\N{\rENG}Who?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.96,1:27:47.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是索菲亞\N{\rENG}I'm Sofia.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.20,1:27:55.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在, 我要確定我系了四次\N{\rENG}Now, I'm gonna make sure that I tie it four times.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.67,1:27:57.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道為什麼嗎, 茱莉?\N{\rENG}You know why,Julie?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.67,1:28:00.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為四次才有意義\N{\rENG}Because four times really means something.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.64,1:28:02.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,大衛, 別傷害我\N{\rENG}David, don't hurt me.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.08,1:28:05.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,我怕了, 你真行\N{\rENG}I'm freaked out. It worked.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.85,1:28:07.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道你這樣是逃不了的...\N{\rENG}You know you're not gonna get away with this...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.98,1:28:09.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴我, 索菲亞在哪\N{\rENG}so tell me now, where is Sofia.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.72,1:28:12.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,我就是索菲亞\N{\rENG}I am Sofia.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.46,1:28:15.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 索菲亞在哪? - 我就是索菲亞!\N{\rENG}- Where's Sofia? - I am Sofia!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.19,1:28:17.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 她在哪?\N{\rENG}- 我就是!\N{\rENG}- Where is she? - I am Sofia!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.69,1:28:20.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要叫員警, 你可以和他們說\N{\rENG}I'm calling the police, and you can tell it to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.26,1:28:22.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你從事故中生還了 - 什麼事故?\N{\rENG}- You survived the accident. - What accident?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.63,1:28:26.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,那是誰的屍體? 是七矮人的董事會, 是嗎?\N{\rENG}Whose body was it? It was the Seven Dwarfs, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.17,1:28:28.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我沒有出事故\N{\rENG}- 你還想搶走我的生活!\N{\rENG}- I wasn't in an accident. - You're trying to steal my life!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.01,1:28:31.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,你當然沒有出事故\N{\rENG}Of course you weren't in an accident.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.24,1:28:33.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在看來你他媽的是想殺我!\N{\rENG}Now it's fucking attempted murder!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.88,1:28:36.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是索菲亞, 求求你\N{\rENG}I'm Sofia. Please.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.48,1:28:40.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,和他們說去\N{\rENG}Tell it to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.32,1:28:42.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是大衛埃姆斯\N{\rENG}This is David Aames.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.65,1:28:44.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,我需要幫助\N{\rENG}I need help.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.15,1:28:46.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,有個入侵者, 我抓住了一個入侵者...\N{\rENG}I have an intruder-\N{\rENG}I've captured an intruder...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.62,1:28:48.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,她闖進我家\N{\rENG}who's entered my home.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.22,1:28:51.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,天, 醒醒, 老兄\N{\rENG}God. Wake up, man.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.93,1:28:55.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是來真的?\N{\rENG}Are you for real?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.57,1:29:07.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓我在這等了三個鐘, 他們什麼都不說\N{\rENG}Kept me waiting here for three hours. They won't even tell me any news.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.78,1:29:10.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,這些傢伙認為這些是我做的\N{\rENG}These guys think that I had something to do with this.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.21,1:29:12.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,給我們一分鐘, 好嗎?\N{\rENG}Give us a minute here, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.28,1:29:16.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,拉爾森探員, 安德魯探員, 謝謝\N{\rENG}Detective Larson, Detective Andrews, thanks very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.36,1:29:20.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們認為是我做的\N{\rENG}They think that I had something to do with this.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.46,1:29:23.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會處理這些, 就像你爸會做的那樣\N{\rENG}I'm gonna handle this exactly the way your father would.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.56,1:29:25.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,我都解決了\N{\rENG}I've got it solved.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.80,1:29:28.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,解決了?\N{\rENG}You got it solved?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.97,1:29:30.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,她在哪?\N{\rENG}Where is she?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.84,1:29:35.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,她會沒事的. 現在, 所有的檔案都會...\N{\rENG}She's gonna be fine. Now, this whole file is gonna-
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.14,1:29:41.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,幸好你在這兒, 老兄\N{\rENG}Thank God you're here, man.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.44,1:29:43.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒事了\N{\rENG}It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.98,1:29:46.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我愛她 - 是的\N{\rENG}- I love her. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.98,1:29:50.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在我要你看看這些照片, 然後我就銷毀它們\N{\rENG}Right now I want you to look at these photos, then I'm gonna destroy them.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.65,1:29:53.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,索菲亞的證詞也在這兒\N{\rENG}Sofia's testimony is also in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.32,1:29:55.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,也將不會存在\N{\rENG}It won't exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.06,1:29:58.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,她將不會再提起指控\N{\rENG}She's not gonna press charges.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.93,1:30:03.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,指控我?\N{\rENG}Press charges against me?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.20,1:30:05.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,大衛, 醒醒\N{\rENG}David, wake up.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.51,1:30:10.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在, 作為一個朋友...\N{\rENG}Now, as a friend...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.94,1:30:14.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,我覺得你應該看看你對索菲亞做了什麼\N{\rENG}I think you should see what you did to Sofia.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.68,1:30:20.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,記者不會找到這裡,如果你快點走的話\N{\rENG}The press won't get hold of this if you get away quickly.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.29,1:30:26.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,湯米, 這是茱莉, 這不是索菲亞\N{\rENG}Tommy, this is Julie. This is not Sofia.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.32,1:30:29.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是茱莉.吉雅妮\N{\rENG}This is Julie Gianni.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.79,1:30:33.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,我沒對她做這些, 湯米, 有人在陷害我\N{\rENG}I didn't do this to her. Tommy, someone's setting me up.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.86,1:30:37.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,大衛, 董事會和我會搞定這一切\N{\rENG}David, the board and I have taken care of everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.03,1:30:41.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,好嗎, 他們很了不起, 真的了不起, 事實上\N{\rENG}Okay, they've been really great, really great, actually.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.97,1:30:44.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,所有這些都將消失\N{\rENG}All this is gonna disappear.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.74,1:30:48.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們都會支援你, 包括董事會\N{\rENG}We're all behind you, even the board.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.76,1:31:02.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,出去吧\N{\rENG}Get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.46,1:31:08.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是一次心靈的革命\N{\rENG}This is a revolution of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.77,1:31:19.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,你還他媽裝悲傷的樣子!\N{\rENG}You're in fuckin' sad shape!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.94,1:31:22.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,別他媽的打女人\N{\rENG}Don't fucking ever hit a girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.95,1:31:25.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,打我, 別他媽的打女人\N{\rENG}Hit me, but don't fucking ever hit a girl!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.02,1:31:27.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽我說, 那不是索菲亞\N{\rENG}Listen to me. It wasn't Sofia.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.02,1:31:30.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,是茱莉\N{\rENG}It was Julie.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.55,1:31:33.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 是茱莉 - 是茱莉.吉雅妮?\N{\rENG}- It was Julie. - It was Julie Gianni.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.69,1:31:35.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.73,1:31:39.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,所以索菲亞是被茱莉綁架了...\N{\rENG}So Sofia was abducted by Julie...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.20,1:31:42.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,然後茱莉扮成索菲亞\N{\rENG}and now Julie is posing as Sofia.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.93,1:31:47.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,你喪心病狂了, 老兄\N{\rENG}You're in O.J. land, man.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.10,1:31:50.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,茱莉吉雅尼已經他媽的死了!\N{\rENG}Julie Gianni is fucking dead!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.41,1:31:54.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不管他們和你說了什麼,我可以向你保證茱莉還活著\N{\rENG}I don't care what they told you, I can assure you Julie Gianni is alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.94,1:31:57.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 她還活著 - 我都沒和員警談過\N{\rENG}- She is alive. - I didn't talk to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.25,1:31:59.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是和索菲亞談的\N{\rENG}I talked to Sofia.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.15,1:32:03.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 她在哪?  - 我剛送她回家\N{\rENG}- Where is she? - I just dropped Sofia off.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.32,1:32:05.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,我看見你對她做的所有事\N{\rENG}I saw everything you did to her.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.22,1:32:08.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,我告訴你, 我沒那樣對她\N{\rENG}Let me tell you something. I did not do that to her.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.39,1:32:12.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,看著我, 看著我的眼睛\N{\rENG}Look at me. Look me in the eye.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.33,1:32:14.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴我, 她就是那個你帶去派對的女孩\N{\rENG}You tell me that's the girl you brought to the party.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:14.66,1:32:17.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴我她就是你的夢中情人...\N{\rENG}You tell me that that's your dream girl...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.73,1:32:19.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,你一時的迷戀\N{\rENG}your proximity infatuation.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.07,1:32:21.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的!\N{\rENG}Yes!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.91,1:32:23.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,而你把她從我這偷走了\N{\rENG}And you stole her from me.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.07,1:32:27.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,我唯一想要的女孩, 你把她偷走了\N{\rENG}The one girl I really wanted, and you took her from me.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.44,1:32:30.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,你瘋了, 你不正常了, 老兄\N{\rENG}You're insane. You're losin' it, man.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.08,1:32:34.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你露出真面目了 - 噢, 是的\N{\rENG}- You have revealed yourself. - Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.02,1:32:36.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,我和他們一夥的\N{\rENG}I'm with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.36,1:32:44.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,你哪兒弄的大衣, 布萊恩?\N{\rENG}Where'd you get the coat, Brian?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.70,1:32:47.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,哪兒得到的像機?\N{\rENG}Where'd you get the camera?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.03,1:32:50.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們付你多少?\N{\rENG}How much did they pay you?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.20,1:32:54.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽著, 這將是我們最後一次談話\N{\rENG}Listen to me, 'cause this is the last time we're ever gonna speak.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.64,1:32:57.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,我曾是你唯一的朋友\N{\rENG}I was your only friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.44,1:33:00.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,你終於露出真面目了\N{\rENG}You have revealed yourself to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.33,1:33:24.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,有問題嗎?\N{\rENG}Problems?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.24,1:33:29.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,我沒心情胡扯, 所以拜託你...\N{\rENG}I'm in no mood to be fucked with, so do yourself a favor-
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.27,1:33:32.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,我能解釋所有這一切, 大衛\N{\rENG}There's an explanation for all this, David.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.01,1:33:37.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們互相認識, 你在網路上找到我\N{\rENG}You and I know each other. You found me on the Internet.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.15,1:33:41.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是來這幫你, 大衛\N{\rENG}I'm here to help you, David.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.85,1:33:47.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,你他媽的是誰? 為什麼跟蹤我?\N{\rENG}Who the fuck are you? Why are you following me?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.39,1:33:51.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,首先, 你一定要冷靜下來\N{\rENG}First of all, it's very important that you calm down.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.00,1:33:54.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,冷靜?\N{\rENG}Calm down?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.03,1:33:57.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,冷靜\N{\rENG}Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.50,1:33:59.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,你必須克服你的恐懼, 做回自己\N{\rENG}You must overcome your fears and regain control.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.04,1:34:02.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,再次掌控你的生活, 大衛\N{\rENG}Take ahold of your life again, David.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.54,1:34:04.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,就像握住那酒杯一樣容易\N{\rENG}It's as easy as holding that glass.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.54,1:34:08.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果我告訴你會怎樣...你可以控制...\N{\rENG}What if I were to tell you that you can take control...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.78,1:34:10.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,所有的這些, 一切\N{\rENG}of all of this, everything?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.95,1:34:12.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,甚至我\N{\rENG}Even me.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.98,1:34:16.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽著, 我不是同性戀, 好嗎?\N{\rENG}Look, I'm straight. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.19,1:34:22.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,大衛, 看看這些人\N{\rENG}David, look at all these people.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.19,1:34:25.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們好像都在聊天, 不是嗎?\N{\rENG}Seems as though they're just all chatting away, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.73,1:34:26.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.90,1:34:29.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 和你沒關係 - 沒錯\N{\rENG}- Nothing to do with you. - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.17,1:34:30.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是...\N{\rENG}And yet...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.80,1:34:34.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許他們在這裡, 只是因為你想要他們在這裡\N{\rENG}maybe they're only here because you wanted them to be here.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.67,1:34:36.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,你就是他們的上帝\N{\rENG}You are their god.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.07,1:34:41.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,不止這樣, 你可以讓他們服從你或毀了你\N{\rENG}Not only that, but you can make them obey you or even destroy you.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.65,1:34:46.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,好吧, 我想讓他們做的就是他媽的閉嘴\N{\rENG}Well, what I'd love for them to do\N{\rENG}is shut the fuck up.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.92,1:34:48.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,尤其是你\N{\rENG}Especially you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.50,1:35:02.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,你看\N{\rENG}You see?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.61,1:35:17.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們簽了一份合約, 大衛\N{\rENG}You and I signed a contract, David.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.51,1:35:21.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,餐館裡的人是誰? 他是誰?\N{\rENG}Who is the man in the restaurant? Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.42,1:35:24.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不知...\N{\rENG}I can't-
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.12,1:35:26.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,你能分清夢境和現實嗎?\N{\rENG}Can you tell the difference between dreams and reality?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.19,1:35:28.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 當然了, 你能嗎?  - 想想看\N{\rENG}- Of course. Can you? - Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.59,1:35:31.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,用腦子想\N{\rENG}Think with your head.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.89,1:35:33.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,你簽了一份合同...\N{\rENG}You signed a contract...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.96,1:35:35.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,到底簽了沒有?\N{\rENG}did you not?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.27,1:35:38.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,我簽了某樣東西\N{\rENG}I signed something.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.87,1:35:40.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,餐館裡的那個人也在嗎?\N{\rENG}Was the man in the restaurant there?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.71,1:35:46.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 操..\N{\rENG}- 順從你身體的抵抗\N{\rENG}- Fuck- Accept your body's resistance.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.21,1:35:48.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,用你的腦子想\N{\rENG}Let your head answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.61,1:35:51.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,簽這合約, 大衛\N{\rENG}Sign the contract, David.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.38,1:35:52.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 是的 - 這就對了\N{\rENG}- Yes. - That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.48,1:35:54.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,艾莉是誰?\N{\rENG}Who is Ellie?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.72,1:36:00.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我不知道什麼是真的 - 那晚發生了什麼?\N{\rENG}- I don't know what's real. - What happened that night?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.56,1:36:04.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 某個人死了- 我不想記得\N{\rENG}- Somebody died. - I don't want to remember.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.13,1:36:06.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,你掌握著解救自己的關鍵\N{\rENG}You hold the keys to this prison.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.10,1:36:09.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 那不是索菲亞 - 那是誰?\N{\rENG}- It wasn't Sofia. - Who was it?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.80,1:36:10.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 不是 - 那是誰?\N{\rENG}- No. - Who was it?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.77,1:36:17.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,我好害怕你這麼厲害\N{\rENG}I'm afraid of how powerful this is.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.47,1:36:21.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,你想要說出來, 不是嗎, 大衛?\N{\rENG}You wanna let it out, don't you, David?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.11,1:36:25.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,你就要說了\N{\rENG}You're about to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.12,1:36:29.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴我...\N{\rENG}Tell me...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:29.15,1:36:32.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的內心和靈魂不會允許你忘記\N{\rENG}what your heart and soul will not allow you to forget.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.76,1:36:37.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,你殺了索菲亞嗎?\N{\rENG}Did you kill Sofia?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.45,1:37:31.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,我以為你是個破壞者\N{\rENG}I thought you were a vandal.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.42,1:37:36.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是誰?\N{\rENG}Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.12,1:37:41.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是索菲亞\N{\rENG}I'm Sofia.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.79,1:37:45.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不是...\N{\rENG}You are not...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.80,1:37:47.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,索菲亞\N{\rENG}Sofia.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.00,1:37:52.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不是..索菲亞\N{\rENG}You are not...Sofia.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.57,1:37:54.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是索菲亞\N{\rENG}I'm Sofia.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.04,1:37:56.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,算了\N{\rENG}Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.61,1:37:59.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們又會在一起了\N{\rENG}We're gonna be together again.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.34,1:38:03.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,你會忘了茱莉, 和我在一起\N{\rENG}You're gonna forget about Juliana and we're gonna be together.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.31,1:38:05.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不會再怕你了\N{\rENG}I'm not gonna be afraid of you anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.42,1:38:09.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,我去給你拿冷毛巾, 馬上回來\N{\rENG}I'm gonna get you a cold towel. I'll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.62,1:38:12.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,我愛你\N{\rENG}I love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.41,1:38:33.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,延遲享樂者\N{\rENG}Pleasure delayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.22,1:38:43.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,索菲亞?\N{\rENG}Sofia?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.71,1:39:04.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是索菲亞\N{\rENG}I am Sofia.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.78,1:39:12.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,我愛你\N{\rENG}I love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.58,1:39:15.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,我太想念你了\N{\rENG}Oh, I missed you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.39,1:39:26.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,你到哪去了?\N{\rENG}Where were you?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.57,1:39:34.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,算了\N{\rENG}Forget it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.37,1:39:36.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不必知道\N{\rENG}I don't need to know.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:37.37,1:39:39.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,這沒什麼\N{\rENG}It doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.08,1:39:43.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,只要告訴我你愛我\N{\rENG}Just tell me that you love me.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.85,1:39:50.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,我愛你\N{\rENG}I love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.12,1:39:55.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,幸福對你來說是什麼, 大衛?\N{\rENG}What is happiness to you, David?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.53,1:39:57.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,對我來說...\N{\rENG}For me...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.79,1:39:59.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,就是在這兒和你在一起\N{\rENG}it's being here with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.20,1:40:08.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,這他媽的...\N{\rENG}What the fuck...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.34,1:40:10.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,是怎麼回事?\N{\rENG}is happening?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.38,1:40:15.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,這他媽的怎麼回事?\N{\rENG}What is fucking happening?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.61,1:40:18.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,大衛真是個可愛的小孩\N{\rENG}David was a real delight as a child.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:22.12,1:40:23.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢, 天哪!\N{\rENG}Oh, God!
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.32,1:40:26.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,我很害怕你真厲害!\N{\rENG}I'm so afraid of how powerful this is!
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.82,1:40:30.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢, 大衛!\N{\rENG}Oh, David!
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.22,1:40:52.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,紅禮服, 系帶鞋?\N{\rENG}Red dress, strappy shoes?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.22,1:41:03.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是我聽過的最棒的話\N{\rENG}That is the greatest thing I've ever heard.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.06,1:41:07.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,下輩子當我們都是貓的時候\N{\rENG}In another life when we are both cats.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:14.10,1:41:15.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,怎麼回事?\N{\rENG}What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.81,1:41:19.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿, 老兄, 怎麼回事?\N{\rENG}Hey, man, what's happening?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.98,1:41:26.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,你這婊子!\N{\rENG}You bitch!
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.12,1:41:31.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不想看見你的臉!\N{\rENG}I don't wanna see your face!
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.79,1:42:41.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,是我幹的, 對吧?\N{\rENG}I did it, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.29,1:42:47.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,但我沒覺得我殺過人\N{\rENG}But I don't feel like I killed someone.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.50,1:42:52.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 大衛... - 我覺得...\N{\rENG}- David... - I feel like...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.33,1:42:55.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 那個男人是誰... - 我像在夢中\N{\rENG}- who was the man... - I'm in a dream.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.14,1:42:57.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,餐館裡的那個?\N{\rENG}at the restaurant?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:15.32,1:43:17.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,有時候...\N{\rENG}Sometimes...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.16,1:43:19.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,大腦的行為讓你覺得就像在做夢\N{\rENG}the mind behaves as if it were in a dream.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.53,1:43:22.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,面孔變換, 一個人變成另一個\N{\rENG}Faces change. People become other people.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:24.70,1:43:27.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,潛意識是很強烈的\N{\rENG}The subconscious is a powerful thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:29.51,1:43:31.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,你對茱莉沒興趣, 不是嗎?\N{\rENG}You treated Julie carelessly, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.05,1:43:45.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,你對她抱有負罪感...\N{\rENG}Your feelings of responsibility or guilt over Julie...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.06,1:43:48.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,很容易把索菲亞當成茱莉\N{\rENG}might have easily turned Sofia into Julie.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.76,1:43:53.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道精神錯亂是什麼嗎?\N{\rENG}Do you know what derangement is?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:54.56,1:43:56.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,我需要你説明\N{\rENG}I need your help.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.23,1:44:01.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,我所知道的就是,你殺了你的女朋友...\N{\rENG}All I know is, you killed your girlfriend...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.17,1:44:04.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不知道你想的是什麼\N{\rENG}and I don't know what's in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:04.11,1:44:05.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,我需要你説明\N{\rENG}I need your help.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:05.71,1:44:09.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會一直跟進這案子如果可以的話, 但我們沒時間了\N{\rENG}I would work on this case forever if I could, but we're out of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:15.05,1:44:16.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,你會以什麼做辯詞?\N{\rENG}What will you plead?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:20.62,1:44:22.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,暫時性神經失常\N{\rENG}Temporary derangement.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:24.03,1:44:25.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是最好的說法\N{\rENG}That's your best chance.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.53,1:44:30.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不認為他們會相信我\N{\rENG}I don't think they'll believe me.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:31.10,1:44:32.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,你相信什麼?\N{\rENG}What do you believe?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.84,1:44:37.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,無論相信什麼, 我很關心你\N{\rENG}Believe it or not, I care about you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:41.98,1:44:44.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,你對我來說已經像家人一樣\N{\rENG}You've become like family to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.85,1:44:52.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不想放棄你, 大衛, 但我需要瞭解更多\N{\rENG}I don't want to give up on you, David, but I needed more.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:52.35,1:44:54.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,我需要...\N{\rENG}I needed-
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.26,1:44:56.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,我需要一個答案\N{\rENG}I needed an answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.49,1:44:59.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的意思是, 我覺得會有一個更好的理由...\N{\rENG}I mean, I even thought there was more than a good chance...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.73,1:45:01.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,有人在陷害你\N{\rENG}somebody was playing a trick on you.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:01.73,1:45:04.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許是董事會\N{\rENG}Maybe it was the board.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.13,1:45:06.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,但這已經超過我的職責\N{\rENG}But I can't exceed my duties.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.87,1:45:13.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,我只是個心理學家\N{\rENG}I'm just a psychologist.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:16.31,1:45:18.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,我也得走了\N{\rENG}And I have to go now.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.22,1:45:24.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,審訊的時候再見?\N{\rENG}Will I see you at the trial?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.16,1:45:27.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,不, 我只...\N{\rENG}No, I'm-
Dialogue: 0,1:45:28.69,1:45:30.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,我只算是個開場\N{\rENG}I'm just the opening act.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:49.55,1:45:53.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,"讓您安心是我們的專長, 這是我們生命延續的信條"\N{\rENG}Reassurance is our specialty. That is the Life Extension credo.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:02.59,1:46:05.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,"班尼是一條曾被凍了三個月的小狗..."\N{\rENG}Benny is a dog who was frozen for three months...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:05.73,1:46:07.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,"解凍後過上了正常的生活"\N{\rENG}and thawed out to live a normal life.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:07.96,1:46:11.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,"生命延續也能用在人類的形式上"\N{\rENG}Life Extension can translate to the human form too.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:12.84,1:46:15.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,"你如何辦到這些?"\N{\rENG}How do you accomplish such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:15.27,1:46:18.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,"72個冷凍的病人..."\N{\rENG}Seventy-two cryonized patients...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.51,1:46:21.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,"目前保存在新不倫瑞克省我們的收容中心裡"\N{\rENG}are currently held at our facility in New Brunswick.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:21.94,1:46:26.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,"我們擁有世界上最好的科技人員"\N{\rENG}And we feature the finest scientific technicians on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:30.12,1:46:31.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,麥凱布醫生!\N{\rENG}McCabe!
Dialogue: 0,1:46:36.43,1:46:38.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,回來!\N{\rENG}Come back!
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.44,1:46:42.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,LE (發音近似Ellie--艾莉)\N{\rENG}LE
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.16,1:47:17.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,生命延續公司\N{\rENG}Life Extension Corporation, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:17.27,1:47:19.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我能幫你嗎?\N{\rENG}- LE - Can I help you? - LE
Dialogue: 0,1:47:19.37,1:47:21.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們有法院許可\N{\rENG}We hold a court order.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:23.71,1:47:25.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想我之前來過這裡\N{\rENG}I think I've been here before.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:38.92,1:47:40.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,她叫莉比\N{\rENG}Her name is Libby.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:40.49,1:47:42.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,早上好, 麥凱布先生\N{\rENG}Good morning, Mr. McCabe.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:42.89,1:47:45.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是莉比, 讓我為你效勞\N{\rENG}I'm Libby. I'm here to assist you.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:46.96,1:47:49.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,他是我兒子, 他很害羞\N{\rENG}He's my son. He's very shy.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:49.97,1:47:54.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不是媒體或法律協會的, 是吧?\N{\rENG}You're not with the media or a part of any legal consortium, correct?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:54.44,1:47:55.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,不是\N{\rENG}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:56.47,1:47:58.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,歡迎來到生命延續\N{\rENG}Welcome to Life Extension.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:58.44,1:48:01.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,看一下我們的簡介, 請跟我來\N{\rENG}Take a look at our proposal. Please follow me.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:01.44,1:48:03.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,你可以在外面等著\N{\rENG}You can wait out here.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:04.45,1:48:06.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們會去見麗蓓嘉.迪爾伯恩...\N{\rENG}You'll be meeting Rebecca Dearborn...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:06.78,1:48:08.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,我心目中的榜樣\N{\rENG}my personal role model.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:10.89,1:48:13.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不想再要痛苦, 我已經受夠了\N{\rENG}I didn't need the pain anymore. I already experienced that.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:13.89,1:48:17.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們想要你倒下死掉, 生命延續想要你生存\N{\rENG}They want you to lay down and die. Life Extension wants you to live.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:20.06,1:48:23.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不認為上帝不同意這麼做\N{\rENG}I don't think that God disapproves of this.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:23.40,1:48:26.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,"冰凍: 覺醒的歷程...\N{\rENG}"Cryonization.: a journey of reawakening...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:27.07,1:48:29.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,首先以超低溫保存人體"\N{\rENG}after the preservation of the human body at extremely low temperatures."
Dialogue: 0,1:48:29.54,1:48:32.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們也曾嘲笑過儒勒·凡爾納 (科幻小說之父)\N{\rENG}They laughed at Jules Verne too.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:32.24,1:48:33.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,大衛, 你不是...\N{\rENG}You are not-
Dialogue: 0,1:48:33.88,1:48:36.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,麥凱布先生, 你好, 我是麗蓓嘉.迪爾伯恩\N{\rENG}Mr. McCabe, how are you? I'm Rebecca Dearborn.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:39.92,1:48:44.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,生命延續, 或者我們更喜歡稱為LE...\N{\rENG}Life Extension, or LE as we like to refer to it...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:44.39,1:48:45.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,是對未來的展望...\N{\rENG}is a glimpse of the future.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:46.56,1:48:47.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,是一張入場券...\N{\rENG}It's a ticket.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:47.89,1:48:51.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,非膚淺的, 而是極有意義的...\N{\rENG}Not in the juvenile sense, but in the deeply meaningful sense...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:51.83,1:48:54.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,深入人類內心的探索\N{\rENG}that can only be born in the human heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:57.23,1:48:59.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,人體的DNA代碼已被破解\N{\rENG}The DNA codes of the human body have been broken.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:00.07,1:49:02.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,很快, 心臟病, 癌症...\N{\rENG}Soon, heart ailments, cancer...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:02.60,1:49:04.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,很多都會成為過去\N{\rENG}so much more will be a thing of the past.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:05.44,1:49:08.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,非常簡單,你的痛苦, 你的不滿...\N{\rENG}Very simply, your anguish, your discontent...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:08.91,1:49:11.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,甚至你的死亡, 都不再發生...\N{\rENG}even your death is no longer necessary...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:11.61,1:49:13.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,...于傳統的概念裡\N{\rENG}in a traditional sense.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:13.45,1:49:17.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,無論是什麼疾病掩藏在那面具後面, 它都是暫時的\N{\rENG}Whatever malady hides behind that mask, it's temporary.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:19.02,1:49:20.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,在你死去一小時內...\N{\rENG}Within an hour of your passing...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:21.02,1:49:24.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,LE將把你的身體轉移到一個容器裡...\N{\rENG}LE will transfer your body to a vessel...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:24.23,1:49:28.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,在那裡你將被密封, 並用-196度低溫冰凍\N{\rENG}where you will be sealed and frozen at 196 degrees below zero.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:28.93,1:49:30.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,斷電, 地震...\N{\rENG}Power outtages, earthquakes-
Dialogue: 0,1:49:30.97,1:49:33.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有任何事會影響你的掛起式休眠\N{\rENG}nothing will affect your suspension hibernation.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:33.57,1:49:36.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,你和這些人簽了合約嗎, 大衛?\N{\rENG}Did you sign a contract with these people, David?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:37.75,1:49:39.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,"清晰夢境"\N{\rENG}"Lucid Dream"
Dialogue: 0,1:49:39.94,1:49:42.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,清晰夢境選項是什麼?\N{\rENG}What's the Lucid Dream option?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:42.88,1:49:44.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,很好的選擇\N{\rENG}Good choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:45.01,1:49:48.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,清晰夢境, 是LE最新的服務選項\N{\rENG}The Lucid Dream is Life Extension's newest option.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:48.48,1:49:50.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,需要額外付一點錢...\N{\rENG}For a little extra...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:50.32,1:49:53.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們提供的這種冰凍結合了...\N{\rENG}we offer the cryonic union...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:53.66,1:49:56.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,科技和享樂的效果\N{\rENG}of science and entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:57.49,1:49:59.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,"冰凍樂"\N{\rENG}"Cryo-tainment."
Dialogue: 0,1:50:03.40,1:50:05.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許這解釋會有幫助\N{\rENG}Some find this presentation helpful.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:11.47,1:50:16.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,# 有一個宇宙 #\N{\rENG}I have a universe
Dialogue: 0,1:50:16.41,1:50:18.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,# 在我心中 #\N{\rENG}Inside me
Dialogue: 0,1:50:18.91,1:50:21.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,現代人一生的寫照\N{\rENG}Portrait of a modern human life.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:21.68,1:50:24.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,美國, 男性...\N{\rENG}American, male...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:24.22,1:50:27.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,出生然後死亡\N{\rENG}birth and death.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:27.19,1:50:30.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,想像你正承受絕症之痛\N{\rENG}Imagine that you are suffering from a terminal illness.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:30.66,1:50:34.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,你想被冰凍, 但你更想被復活...\N{\rENG}You'd like to be cryonized, but you'd rather be resurrected...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:34.16,1:50:37.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,繼續目前你所熟悉的生活\N{\rENG}to continue your own life as you know it now.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:37.50,1:50:40.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,LE會滿足你的要求\N{\rENG}LE offers you the answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:40.87,1:50:42.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,一旦復活...\N{\rENG}Upon resurrection...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:42.50,1:50:45.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,你將繼續以永恆的狀態...\N{\rENG}you will continue in an ageless state...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:45.17,1:50:48.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,...保持下去, 那時的生活...\N{\rENG}preserved but living in the present...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:48.28,1:50:50.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,就是你所選擇的未來\N{\rENG}with a future of your choosing.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:51.11,1:50:54.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,死亡將從你的記憶中抹去\N{\rENG}Your death will be wiped from your memory.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:54.12,1:50:57.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的生活將會是一個現實的藝術品...\N{\rENG}Your life will continue as a realistic work of art...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:57.12,1:50:59.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,...由你所描繪, 每個時刻...\N{\rENG}painted by you, minute to minute...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:59.55,1:51:03.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,...你將活在夏日的浪漫戀情中\N{\rENG}and you'll live it with the romantic abandon of a summer day...
Dialogue: 0,1:51:03.46,1:51:06.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,感覺有如你所喜愛的經典電影...\N{\rENG}with the feeling of a great movie...
Dialogue: 0,1:51:06.23,1:51:08.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,或流行音樂一樣\N{\rENG}or a pop song you always loved-
Dialogue: 0,1:51:08.73,1:51:10.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,有關這是如何發生的記憶...\N{\rENG}with no memory of how it all occurred...
Dialogue: 0,1:51:10.67,1:51:12.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,都不會被保存下來...\N{\rENG}save for the knowledge...
Dialogue: 0,1:51:12.63,1:51:16.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,一切都只是更完美\N{\rENG}that everything simply improved.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:16.84,1:51:18.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,有任何疑惑的地方...\N{\rENG}In any instance of discontent...
Dialogue: 0,1:51:18.84,1:51:21.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,你都會獲得技術支援\N{\rENG}you'll be visited by technical support.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:21.68,1:51:23.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,一切指日可待\N{\rENG}It's all just around the corner.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:23.55,1:51:28.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,在不久的將來, 另一個篇章將無縫的展開\N{\rENG}The day after tomorrow, another chapter begins seamlessly.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:29.05,1:51:30.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,一個逼真的夢境\N{\rENG}A living dream.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:31.05,1:51:33.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,生命延續將向您提供\N{\rENG}[ 清晰夢境 ]\N{\rENG}Life Extension's promise to you. "Lucid Dream"
Dialogue: 0,1:51:33.66,1:51:35.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,生命, 第二章\N{\rENG}Life, part two.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:35.66,1:51:37.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,一個逼真的夢境\N{\rENG}A living dream.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:40.30,1:51:43.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,"死亡將從你的記憶中抹去"\N{\rENG}"Your death will be wiped from your memory."
Dialogue: 0,1:51:43.90,1:51:45.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,我覺得我錯過了<今日美國>的這篇的報導\N{\rENG}I guess I missed that one in USA Today.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:46.03,1:51:47.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,夢境\N{\rENG}A dream.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:49.91,1:51:52.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,要是出錯了呢?\N{\rENG}What if there was a mistake?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:52.94,1:51:55.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,美夢變成了噩夢怎麼辦?\N{\rENG}What if the dream became a nightmare?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:57.25,1:52:00.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然你的潛意識總在干擾你\N{\rENG}Of course your subconscious can always play tricks on you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:02.48,1:52:05.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,它是個力量很強的東西\N{\rENG}The subconscious is a very powerful thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:09.52,1:52:12.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,你和這些人簽合同了嗎, 大衛?\N{\rENG}Did you sign a contract with these people, David?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:12.29,1:52:14.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是個嚴肅的生意\N{\rENG}But this is a serious business.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:16.43,1:52:19.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,"清晰夢境"值得去冒險\N{\rENG}The Lucid Dream is worth the risk.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:20.80,1:52:23.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,生命不去追求夢想那會是什麼?\N{\rENG}And what is any life if not the pursuit of a dream?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:24.64,1:52:26.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,夢想著和平...\N{\rENG}The dream of peace...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:26.21,1:52:28.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,夢想著成就...\N{\rENG}the dream of achievement...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.41,1:52:33.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,夢想有人和你說那些話語...\N{\rENG}the dream of hearing someone say these words...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:33.72,1:52:36.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,當你聽到她們真心的說...\N{\rENG}when they really, truly mean them.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.09,1:52:41.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,我愛你, 大衛\N{\rENG}I love you, David.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:44.83,1:52:45.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,我愛你\N{\rENG}I love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:49.56,1:52:51.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,釋放自己, 大衛\N{\rENG}Roam free, David.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:51.50,1:52:54.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們大多數人的一生...\N{\rENG}Most of us live our whole lives...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:54.37,1:52:57.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,都沒有真正的冒險是屬於自己的\N{\rENG}without any real adventure to call our own.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:57.67,1:53:00.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,這令人難以理解\N{\rENG}It's hard to comprehend.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:00.61,1:53:04.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,"但人們也嘲笑過儒勒.凡爾納" (大衛剛說過)\N{\rENG}"But they laughed at Jules Verne too."
Dialogue: 0,1:53:05.91,1:53:07.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,這...\N{\rENG}This...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:07.32,1:53:08.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,是一場革命...\N{\rENG}is a revolution...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:08.82,1:53:10.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,...關於心靈的\N{\rENG}of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:31.31,1:53:33.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要醒過來!\N{\rENG}I wanna wake up!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:34.04,1:53:35.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,技術員!\N{\rENG}Tech support!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:36.45,1:53:37.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿, 怪物!\N{\rENG}Hey! Face!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:39.61,1:53:42.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是個噩夢!\N{\rENG}It's a nightmare!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:58.67,1:54:01.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,技術員!\N{\rENG}Tech support!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:16.92,1:54:20.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,技術員!\N{\rENG}Tech support!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:56.66,1:54:58.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,大衛.埃姆斯\N{\rENG}David Aames.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:59.43,1:55:01.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想是時候正式的自我介紹了\N{\rENG}I think it's time we had a proper reintroduction.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:01.93,1:55:05.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是艾德蒙.文圖拉, 來自綠洲計畫\N{\rENG}I'm Edmund Ventura from the Oasis Project.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:05.20,1:55:07.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,原名生命延續, LE Formerly Life Extension, LE.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:07.64,1:55:09.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 技術員\N{\rENG}- 是的\N{\rENG}- Tech support. - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:09.77,1:55:11.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的, 我是你的技術支援...\N{\rENG}Yes, I'm your tech support...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:11.77,1:55:15.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們第一次見面是在150年前\N{\rENG}and we first met 150 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:15.28,1:55:17.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,哇, 靠\N{\rENG}Oh, shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:17.71,1:55:19.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,你向我推銷清晰夢境\N{\rENG}You sold me the Lucid Dream.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:21.95,1:55:23.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,他媽的發生了什麼事?\N{\rENG}What the hell happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:23.79,1:55:26.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,我試圖在酒吧裡警告你\N{\rENG}I tried to warn you in the bar.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:26.22,1:55:30.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,我告訴你必須運用控制, 一切取決於你的意志\N{\rENG}I told you you must exercise control, that it all depended on your mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:31.03,1:55:32.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,所有這些...\N{\rENG}All of this...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:32.63,1:55:34.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,都是你的想像創造出來的\N{\rENG}everything is your creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:34.93,1:55:37.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在我們將迎來你抉擇的時刻\N{\rENG}And now we're heading toward your true moment of choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:38.87,1:55:40.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,抉擇的時刻?\N{\rENG}True moment of choice?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:40.67,1:55:41.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:46.91,1:55:48.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,我什麼時候開始清晰夢境的?\N{\rENG}When did the Lucid Dream begin?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:49.01,1:55:50.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,記得夜總會那天嗎?\N{\rENG}Remember the day of the nightclub?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:51.01,1:55:52.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們很快會再見的\N{\rENG}We'll meet up soon.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:54.25,1:55:57.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,那晚, 索菲亞離開後你睡倒在路邊...\N{\rENG}That night, after Sofia left you and you fell asleep on the pavement...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:57.89,1:56:01.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,就是那個時刻, 你選擇作為拼接\N{\rENG}that was the moment that you chose for the splice.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:01.26,1:56:04.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 拼接?\N{\rENG}- 拼接\N{\rENG}- Splice? - Splice.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:04.16,1:56:07.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,記憶中真實生活的結束, 清晰夢境的開始\N{\rENG}The end of your real life and the beginning of LE's Lucid Dream.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:07.86,1:56:10.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,對接過去了很多很多年...\N{\rENG}A splice of many, many years which passed...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:10.87,1:56:13.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,期間你都是在冰凍和夢中\N{\rENG}while you were frozen and dreaming.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:13.30,1:56:15.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,那個時刻你從街上醒來...\N{\rENG}From the moment you woke up on that street...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:15.64,1:56:17.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,就沒有任何傳統觀念上的真實了\N{\rENG}nothing was real in the traditional sense.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:17.94,1:56:19.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,睜開你的眼睛\N{\rENG}Open your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:19.47,1:56:22.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的清晰夢境一直被"生命延續"監控...\N{\rENG}Your Lucid Dream is monitored by Life Extension...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:22.48,1:56:25.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,一個專家小組在跟蹤你的每個想法...\N{\rENG}and a panel of experts who are following your every thought...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:25.78,1:56:27.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,包括這個時刻\N{\rENG}even at this moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:29.88,1:56:31.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,抱歉, 搞得你很頭大\N{\rENG}Forgive me. I'm blowing your mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:35.96,1:56:37.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,我可不喜歡這麼高\N{\rENG}I'm not a big fan of heights.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:39.36,1:56:40.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道\N{\rENG}I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:40.96,1:56:43.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們從你記憶中消除了實際發生的事\N{\rENG}We erased what really happened from your memory.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:44.30,1:56:46.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 消除? - 是替換...\N{\rENG}- Erased? - Replaced.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:46.87,1:56:48.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,...用一個更好的生活\N{\rENG}By a better life...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:48.54,1:56:50.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,在這個...\N{\rENG}under these...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:50.31,1:56:52.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,美麗的...莫内所鍾愛的天空下\N{\rENG}beautiful, Monet-like skies.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:54.21,1:56:55.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,我母親的最愛\N{\rENG}My mother's favorite.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:56.54,1:57:00.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,更好的生活...因為你擁有索菲亞\N{\rENG}A better life because you had Sofia.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:00.15,1:57:04.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,你用年輕時的記憶構築著你的夢\N{\rENG}You sculpted your Lucid Dream out of the iconography of your youth.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:04.29,1:57:07.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,比如一張曾讓你感動的唱片封面\N{\rENG}An album cover that once moved you.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:07.79,1:57:08.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,唱片封面?\N{\rENG}An album cover?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:08.99,1:57:10.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,"有些事...\N{\rENG}There are some things...
Dialogue: 0,1:57:10.36,1:57:13.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,你還沒到年齡去瞭解"\N{\rENG}that you're not old enough to understand just yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:13.36,1:57:17.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,一些電影向你展示了父親是怎樣的...\N{\rENG}A movie you saw once that showed you what a father could be like...
Dialogue: 0,1:57:28.24,1:57:30.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,...或者愛是怎樣的\N{\rENG}or what love could be like.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:30.75,1:57:32.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,而某個女孩...\N{\rENG}This was a kind woman...
Dialogue: 0,1:57:32.38,1:57:35.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,特別的...\N{\rENG}an individual...
Dialogue: 0,1:57:35.22,1:57:37.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,...超過你的想像\N{\rENG}more than your equal.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:37.55,1:57:41.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,你只在現實中認識她, 但在夢中...\N{\rENG}You barely knew her in real life, but in your Lucid Dream...
Dialogue: 0,1:57:41.69,1:57:43.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,...她是你的精神寄託\N{\rENG}she was your savior.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:48.06,1:57:51.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,現實中我怎麼了? 發生了些事\N{\rENG}What happened in my real life? Something happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:51.30,1:57:52.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,你消除了什麼?\N{\rENG}What did you erase?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:52.80,1:57:54.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,你真想知道?\N{\rENG}Do you really want to know?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:56.87,1:57:58.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,把一切告訴我\N{\rENG}Tell me everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:59.64,1:58:02.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,夜總會的第二天早晨, 你在街上醒來...\N{\rENG}The morning after the nightclub, you woke up on that street...
Dialogue: 0,1:58:02.64,1:58:04.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,一個人還帶著宿醉\N{\rENG}hung over and alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:04.55,1:58:06.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,你站起來, 然後離開\N{\rENG}You got up, walked away.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:07.42,1:58:09.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,你再也沒見過索菲亞\N{\rENG}You never saw Sofia again.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:16.06,1:58:18.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,我沒殺索菲亞\N{\rENG}I didn't kill Sofia.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:19.74,1:58:21.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有\N{\rENG}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:21.56,1:58:25.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,你為了控制公司與董事會對抗\N{\rENG}You battled your board for control of the company...
Dialogue: 0,1:58:26.60,1:58:29.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,最後是湯瑪斯.提普, 你父親的朋友...\N{\rENG}and in the end it was Thomas Tipp, your father's friend...
Dialogue: 0,1:58:29.57,1:58:31.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,...你保住他工作的那個人...\N{\rENG}the man whose job you saved...
Dialogue: 0,1:58:31.41,1:58:34.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,...讓公司回到你的控制\N{\rENG}who wrenched the company back into your control.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:35.34,1:58:36.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,湯米\N{\rENG}Tommy.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:38.31,1:58:39.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,可是後來...\N{\rENG}But then...
Dialogue: 0,1:58:40.95,1:58:43.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,有人...死了\N{\rENG}somebody died.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:45.85,1:58:48.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,你思念索菲亞\N{\rENG}You longed for Sofia.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:48.42,1:58:50.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,與世隔絕數月\N{\rENG}You shut yourself away for months.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:50.69,1:58:52.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,你感到孤獨\N{\rENG}You were alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:52.36,1:58:55.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,你再也忍受不了頭痛的痛苦\N{\rENG}You couldn't stand the pain anymore, the headaches.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:56.03,1:58:57.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,你幾乎崩潰\N{\rENG}You could barely function.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:58.60,1:59:00.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,我在網路上找到你\N{\rENG}I found you on the Internet.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:04.61,1:59:07.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,我和你簽了份合同然後...\N{\rENG}I signed a contract with you, and then-
Dialogue: 0,1:59:28.63,1:59:30.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,我記得了\N{\rENG}I remember.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:39.71,1:59:41.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,有人死了\N{\rENG}Somebody died.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:43.34,1:59:44.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,那就是我\N{\rENG}It was me.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:52.05,1:59:55.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,十二月晚些時候...\N{\rENG}And on a day in late December...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:55.32,1:59:57.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,你把自己交給我們\N{\rENG}you gave yourself to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:59.86,2:00:02.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,你進入了休眠的狀態\N{\rENG}You're now in a suspended state.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:06.53,2:00:10.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的朋友布萊恩.謝比在你的舊屋子舉辦了三天紀念會\N{\rENG}Your friend Brian Shelby threw a three-day memorial in your old home.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:11.11,2:00:13.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,他是個真正的朋友\N{\rENG}He was a true friend.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:22.55,2:00:24.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,大家都想念你, 大衛\N{\rENG}You were missed, David.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:47.01,2:00:50.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,索菲亞始終沒能從悲傷中恢復過來\N{\rENG}It was Sofia who never fully recovered.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:51.81,2:00:54.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,她似乎是最瞭解你的人...\N{\rENG}It was she who somehow knew you best...
Dialogue: 0,2:00:55.82,2:00:58.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,和你一樣, 她永遠也忘不了那個晚上...\N{\rENG}and like you, she never forgot that one night...
Dialogue: 0,2:00:58.82,2:01:01.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,真愛幾乎就要出現\N{\rENG}where true love seemed possible.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:10.47,2:01:13.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,往往最重要的, 大衛...\N{\rENG}Consequences, David.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:29.42,2:01:32.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,...都是那些小事\N{\rENG}It's the little things.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:35.76,2:01:37.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,小事\N{\rENG}The little things.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:39.19,2:01:41.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,根本就沒什麼大事, 是吧?\N{\rENG}There's nothing bigger, is there?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:50.51,2:01:53.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的潛意識的確造成了麻煩\N{\rENG}Your subconscious did create problems.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:55.34,2:01:57.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,美夢變成了噩夢\N{\rENG}Your dream turned into a nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:58.75,2:02:01.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,不過現在問題解決了\N{\rENG}The glitch has been corrected.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:02.75,2:02:05.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,所以我只要想像某個事物\N{\rENG}So all I have to do is imagine something.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:05.49,2:02:07.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,比如, 如果我要...\N{\rENG}Like, if I wanted...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:07.49,2:02:09.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,麥凱布現在就回來\N{\rENG}McCabe to come back right now-
Dialogue: 0,2:02:13.49,2:02:15.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽著\N{\rENG}Listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:15.40,2:02:17.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,這些人很危險\N{\rENG}These people are dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:18.37,2:02:21.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們有麻煩了, 現在必須離開這屋頂 \N{\rENG}We're in trouble. We need to get off this roof now.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:25.27,2:02:27.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在我們暫停...\N{\rENG}We're now on pause...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:27.28,2:02:29.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,你將回到你的夢中\N{\rENG}and you're about to return to your Lucid Dream.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:29.88,2:02:31.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,所有事都會更新...\N{\rENG}With all the upgrades...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:31.81,2:02:33.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不會記得所有這些...\N{\rENG}you won't remember any of this...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:33.82,2:02:36.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,也不會為這次技術支援付費\N{\rENG}nor will you be charged for technical support.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:36.68,2:02:39.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在就是你抉擇的時刻\N{\rENG}It's now your moment of choice.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:40.32,2:02:43.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,你可以回到夢中過著美麗的生活...\N{\rENG}You can return to your Lucid Dream and live a beautiful life...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:43.93,2:02:47.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,...和索菲亞或者你希望的任何人\N{\rENG}with Sofia or whomever you wish...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:47.86,2:02:51.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,或者你可以選擇這外面的世界\N{\rENG}or you can choose the world out there.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:53.27,2:02:55.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,"外面的世界"\N{\rENG}"The world out there."
Dialogue: 0,2:02:56.70,2:02:58.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,你可以讓我回到...\N{\rENG}And you can bring me back...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:58.71,2:03:00.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,就像小狗班尼那樣?\N{\rENG}just like Benny the dog?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:00.88,2:03:01.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:02.04,2:03:05.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,就像小狗班尼那樣\N{\rENG}Just like Benny the dog.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:06.38,2:03:08.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然現在你的臉和身體都能被復原\N{\rENG}Your face and body can be fixed now, of course.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:10.05,2:03:13.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,但現實事情會大不一樣\N{\rENG}But things are very different now...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:13.55,2:03:15.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的財富不會一直持有\N{\rENG}and your finances won't last long.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:17.16,2:03:20.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,觀察小組正等待你的決定\N{\rENG}Your panel of observers are waiting for you to choose.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:25.23,2:03:27.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,這沒有任何保證...\N{\rENG}There are no guarantees...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:27.24,2:03:28.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,但記住...\N{\rENG}but remember...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:28.64,2:03:30.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,即使是在未來...\N{\rENG}even in the future...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:30.77,2:03:33.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,甜蜜也不會是甜蜜...\N{\rENG}the sweet is never as sweet...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:33.81,2:03:36.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,...如果沒嘗過心酸的話\N{\rENG}without the sour.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:54.13,2:03:55.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,我該怎麼醒過來?\N{\rENG}How do I wake up?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:56.26,2:03:58.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是你決定的\N{\rENG}The decision is yours.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:03.10,2:04:05.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,這個地方也是我選擇的, 不是嗎?\N{\rENG}And I chose this scenario, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,2:04:07.34,2:04:12.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的, 去面對你僅存的對高度的恐懼\N{\rENG}Yes, to face your last remaining fear of heights.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:12.41,2:04:14.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,大衛, 別信他們\N{\rENG}David, don't listen to him.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:14.45,2:04:17.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,你說得對, 這都是七矮人, 這是個圈套\N{\rENG}You were right. This is the seven dwarfs. It's a setup!
Dialogue: 0,2:04:17.45,2:04:19.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不能相信他\N{\rENG}You can't trust him.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:19.99,2:04:24.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,別為他感到不爽, 大衛, 這人是你創造出來的\N{\rENG}Don't feel bad for him, David. This winning man is your creation.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:24.19,2:04:28.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,他本能的去爭取他的存在, 但他不是真的\N{\rENG}It's in his nature to fight for his existence, but he's not real.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:28.20,2:04:29.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是真的\N{\rENG}I'm real.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:32.47,2:04:33.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是真的\N{\rENG}I'm real.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:34.54,2:04:36.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,我有兩個女兒...\N{\rENG}I have two daughters...
Dialogue: 0,2:04:36.64,2:04:38.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道的\N{\rENG}and you know that.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:39.27,2:04:40.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,她們的名字是什麼?\N{\rENG}What are their names?
Dialogue: 0,2:04:55.66,2:04:57.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是真的\N{\rENG}I'm real.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:02.26,2:05:05.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,我只是家庭娛樂的犧牲品?\N{\rENG}I'm mortality as home entertainment?
Dialogue: 0,2:05:05.43,2:05:07.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,這不可能是我的命運\N{\rENG}This cannot be the future!
Dialogue: 0,2:05:09.80,2:05:10.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,可能嗎?\N{\rENG}Can it?
Dialogue: 0,2:05:12.97,2:05:14.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,可能嗎?\N{\rENG}Can it?
Dialogue: 0,2:05:42.77,2:05:44.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,再見\N{\rENG}Good-bye.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:47.54,2:05:50.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是一場自我覺醒的偉大旅程\N{\rENG}It's been a brilliant journey of self-awakening.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:50.91,2:05:54.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在你只需要問問自己\N{\rENG}And now you've simply got to ask yourself this-
Dialogue: 0,2:05:54.38,2:05:56.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,幸福對你來說是什麼, 大衛?\N{\rENG}What is happiness to you, David?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:03.93,2:06:06.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想過真實的生活\N{\rENG}I want to live a real life.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:07.50,2:06:09.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不想再做夢\N{\rENG}I don't want to dream any longer.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:10.93,2:06:13.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,最後還有什麼願望嗎?\N{\rENG}Any last wishes?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:15.60,2:06:19.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,就讓他們知道我的想法吧\N{\rENG}Let them out there read my mind.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:19.77,2:06:21.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,祝你好運, 大衛\N{\rENG}I wish you well, David.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:01.98,2:07:04.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,瞧瞧我們\N{\rENG}Look at us.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:04.39,2:07:06.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,我被冰凍, 你卻死了\N{\rENG}I'm frozen, and you're dead.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:07.49,2:07:09.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,而我愛你\N{\rENG}And I love you.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:11.03,2:07:12.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是個問題\N{\rENG}It's a problem.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:16.36,2:07:18.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,我上了那輛車後就失去了你\N{\rENG}I lost you when I got in that car.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:19.87,2:07:21.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,對不起\N{\rENG}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:23.67,2:07:26.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,你還記得曾經對我說過的嗎?\N{\rENG}Do you remember what you told me once?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:27.51,2:07:29.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,每一分鐘...\N{\rENG}That every passing minute...
Dialogue: 0,2:07:30.91,2:07:33.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,都有可能會改變一切\N{\rENG}is another chance to turn it all around.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:39.25,2:07:41.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會再找到你的\N{\rENG}I'll find you again.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:57.87,2:08:00.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,下輩子我會再遇見你...\N{\rENG}I'll see you in another life...
Dialogue: 0,2:08:00.57,2:08:02.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,當我們都是貓的時候\N{\rENG}when we are both cats.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:14.98,2:09:16.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,放輕鬆, 大衛\N{\rENG}Relax, David.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:17.02,2:09:18.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,睜開你的眼睛\N{\rENG}Open your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:28.50,2:09:36.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,追悼會上那首歌名是: (我們漂浮在宇宙中)\N{\rENG}Ladies And Gentlemen We Are Floating In Space

